title: light macaroni and cheese italiano(lo-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large pot, bring water and bouillon to a boil. Add pasta and boil 8 minutes or until just done; drain well. Spray a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish with nonstick vegetable oil.
Place half the pasta in dish and cover with half of the ham strips.
Repeat with the remaining pasta and ham.
Combine milk, egg substitute, flour, salt and pepper; pour over pasta and ham.
Sprinkle with both cheeses and bake about 30 minutes or until custard is set and casserole is lightly browned. Makes 8 servings.

title: grandmother sauls' fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover with cornmeal.
Fry slowly in heated bacon drippings until browned.
Turn once.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Pour oil into electric skillet to about 1/2 to 1 inch deep. Heat to 375 degrees.
Combine the eggs and milk in a mixing bowl. Beat until blended. Add sugar and flour.
Beat until smooth. Cover the bottom of the funnel with your finger.
Pour about 1/4 to 1/3 cup of the batter into funnel.
Hold the funnel over the skillet. Remove your finger and release the batter in a spiral motion.
Fry until golden brown on one side.
Carefully turn the funnel cake over and brown the other side.
Remove from oil and drain well on paper towels.
Sprinkle generously with powdered sugar.
Repeat with remaining batter.
Serve warm.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Mix and roll out. Fill with fruit. Fold and fry in deep fat at 375°. Needs no flour for rolling. Fruit should be cold.

title: blueberry cupcakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed; folding in berries gently. Bake at 375 for 25 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add bell pepper and onion.
Cook until tender (do not brown).
Add milk to corn.
Remove pepper and onion from margarine.
Crush saltines and add to margarine.
Mix well.
Put saltines in corn mixture.
Save some for topping.
Put in Pyrex dish and put saltine crumbs on top.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: raw apple cake *
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add and beat eggs.
Sift together soda, salt, cinnamon and flour.
Add to butter mixture.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in an oblong pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: helen keller's green dessert
directions: This can also be made using orange juice, orange jello and the vanilla ice cream.

title: huevos a la flamenca(eggs flamenco)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil until tender; add sausage, cut in slices or ham and cook until lightly browned.
Add parsley and diced pimentos; cook about 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt and chicken broth; simmer until sauce is well blended.
Divide sauce in four parts; pour into 4 shallow ramekins.
Break
two eggs into each.
Arrange cooked peas and asparagus around eggs, pushing down into sauce.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until eggs are just set, about 20 minutes.
Serve at once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: carol's peach parfait
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups water.
Add 1 can fruit and juice (frozen strawberries).
Place in refrigerator until soft set (1 to 2 hours).
Stir occasionally.
In blender, combine mixture with cream cheese.
In large bowl, mix in Cool Whip with whisk. Refrigerate.
Garnish.
Serve.
Can use any combo of fruit and jello.
Color of jello determines color of parfait.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: Sift flour with sugar; add cranberries, walnuts and grated orange peel.
Combine beaten egg and Wesson oil with orange juice. Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moist.
Bake in greased loaf pan in 350° oven for 50 minutes or until done (check after 40 to 45 minutes).
Remove from pan and cool.

title: quick garden cheese soup(makes about 2 quarts)
directions: In large kettle, cook celery and onion in margarine until tender; stir in flour.
Gradually add water, then remaining ingredients except milk and cheese; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook and stir until soup is hot (do not boil).
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: fourth of july fruit cake
directions: Mix margarine, Crisco, sugar, almond extract, baking powder and vanilla together for 3 minutes on slow speed, 3 minutes on high speed.
Add flour.
Spread 2/3 of batter on a greased cookie sheet.
Add cherry and blueberry pie filling.
Top with rest of the batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Use long jelly roll pan.

title: jan's bean salad
directions: Put in saucepan; stir constantly.
Cook until clear and thick. Cool, then mix over vegetables.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown celery, onions and peppers together in oil until soft. Brown meat; add ingredients to the browned meat and let simmer 40 minutes to 1 hour.

title: old timey strawberry preserves
directions: Wash and hull strawberries.
Add sugar. Heat gently until sugar dissolves so juice is drawn from berries.
Cook rapidly until syrup is thick.
Pack in sterilized jars.
Seal.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Bring sugar, Milnot and oleo for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add chips and Marshmallow Creme (to taste).
Also add peanut butter at this time if you used butterscotch chips.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and let set.

title: hungarian noodle casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Sprinkle paprika and Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour or longer.
Good with ham.

title: fruit pie
directions: Sift all together; add enough milk for batter, not too thick. Melt 1/2 stick oleo in a Pyrex dish.
Pour batter over melted oleo and pour on fruit (of your choice).
Bake in moderate oven until brown.

title: meatless meatballs
directions: Grind walnuts finely. Mix together walnuts, oats, eggs, sage and salt. Form into balls. Heat olive oil in frypan and brown "meatballs". Transfer meatballs to a shallow casserole and pour sauce over. Cover and bake in a 350° oven approximately 20 to 25 minutes. Remove cover last 5 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs well.
Cream the butter and sugars together and add vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Stir all together with chips and M&M's. Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet and bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Combine in blender until smooth.
Chill before serving.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; mix in sour cream.
Beat real well. Add eggs, one at a time, then add flour.
Mix and beat well.
Put in a floured and greased tube pan.
Start in a cold oven; bake in a 275° or 300° oven for 2 hours.

title: chicken with lemon sauce
directions: Heat oil and saute garlic until light brown. Add chicken strips and saute about 5 minutes. Remove chicken and most of the oil.
Add mushrooms and butter. Saute until mushrooms are a little brown. Return chicken to pan along with lemon juice, parsley, pepper, oregano and broth.
Simmer until hot and serve over pasta. Makes 4 servings.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: In large Ziploc bag, mix well all the dry ingredients.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
Rinse potatoes; place in flour mixture. Place in baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes on each side.

title: chicken and vegetable casserole
directions: Spray an 8 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Arrange chicken pieces, vegetables and raisins.
Mix gravy mix and 3/4 cup of water and pour over chicken and vegetables.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Serves 5.

title: icicle cucumber pickles
directions: Wash and cut into thin slices the 3 pounds of cucumbers.
Soak in ice water 4 hours.
Drain and pack into sterilized pint jars. Add 1 sliced onion to each jar, and 1/2 teaspoon mustard seed.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Crumble bacon on bottom of pie shell.
Saute onions in butter until golden.
Put into pie shell.
Combine cheese, flour, salt and cayenne.
Stir in the milk and eggs.
Pour over onions and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: caribbean bananas
directions: Melt butter.
Peel bananas and split lengthwise.
Simmer banana gently in butter, both sides.
Baste with sauce.
Serve on hot plate.
Pour rum or liquor over bananas and light.
Can use bananas, peaches or pears.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake batter as directed.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle coconut on bottom of cake pan; sprinkle chopped pecans on top of coconut.
Pour cake batter over top.

title: master mix biscuits
directions: Mix until blended.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead 15 strokes.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Makes 15 to 20.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix two minutes in mixer. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes. Cool 5 minutes and frost in pans.

title: snickerdoodle cookies(frances hindle's recipe)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to shortening mixture and mix well.
Chill dough.
Form dough in small balls and roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: sugarless banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Blend bananas, apple juice and eggs.
Stir in flour mixture, raisins and nuts.
Mix until well blended.
Bake in a 9 x 4-inch greased pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate dipped fruit
directions: Over hot water melt chocolate morsels and shortening.
Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat, but keep over hot water.
Dip pieces of fruit into chocolate; shake off excess.
Place on foil lined cookie sheets.
Chill 10 to 15 minutes until chocolate is set.
Peel off foil.
Fruit may be kept at room temperature up to 1 hour.
If chocolate becomes sticky, return to refrigerator.

title: deluxe german potato salad
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Drain, reserving 1/4 cup drippings. Crumble bacon and set aside. Saute the celery and onion in drippings until tender. Combine sugar and flour; add to skillet with vinegar, water, salt and mustard. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.

title: triple chocolate brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch pie pan.
Mix and beat eggs. Blend in sugar and margarine.
Sift together flour, cocoa and salt; add to egg mixture, beating until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.

title: corn and tomato casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Cook mostaccioli as directed on package until tender.
Marinate in all remaining ingredients in refrigerator for 12 hours or overnight.
Serve chilled.

title: boiled scallops
directions: Boil for 15 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together, adding mayonnaise to texture.

title: granola whip
directions: First you take the chocolate chip granola bars (Sunbelt works the best).
Take a spoon and cover the granola bar with the Cool Whip.
Make sure that you cover all the granola bar.

title: fluffy-fruit 'n cream salad
directions: Drain orange sections, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 3/4 cup liquid.
In saucepan, combine sugar and gelatin.
Add syrup mixture, orange and lemon juice.
Heat until gelatin is dissolved; gradually stir about half of the hot mixture into eggs. Return all to saucepan.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat; add sour cream and cream cheese.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in orange sections, banana and nuts.
Turn into 5 1/2 cup ring mold.
Chill overnight.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon and cheese, together.
Put bacon and cheese over top.

title: melon and mango parfait
directions: Water must be at a full rolling boil and should be freshly drawn.
Water which has come to the boil more than once makes the tea a poor colour and spoils the flavour.
Water must be poured onto the tea while it is still at boiling point.
The tea-pot, jug or carafe should be warmed first.
If served with half-and-half or milk, allow tea to stand for 3 to 5 minutes; serve immediately, if served with slices of lemon.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Melt together white chocolate and peanut butter.
Add peanuts and Rice Krispies.
Mix well but gently.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let set an hour.
Makes approximately 7 dozen cookies.

title: holiday bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin; set aside.
Combine flour, spices, baking soda and salt.
Make well in center and combine with egg mixture until moistened.
Stir in chopped cranberries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (lightly grease and flour loaf pans).
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: dutch apple dessert
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart baking dish, melt margarine.
Sprinkle in crumbs and mix together.
Press in bottom of dish.
Mix together sweetened condensed milk, sour cream and lemon juice.
Spread on top of crumbs.
Spoon pie filling on next.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nuts.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: millionaire's cake
directions: Make cake according to recipe but substitute the water with the pineapple juice from the can of pineapple.
Spread cake evenly in an 8 x 12-inch cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Watch cake carefully since it's thin and oven temperatures vary.
Cool completely.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs; beat 1 minute at medium speed. Combine flour with egg mixture.
Add apples, vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for an hour to an hour and a half.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water and cool.
Add marshmallows. Blend mayo and cream cheese together, add to gelatin mixture.
Add well drained pineapple and nuts; mix well. Fold in whipped cream. Chill for several hours before serving.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and flour; add pecans and mix well. Shape 1 tablespoon per cookie into balls; place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Combine confectioners and granulated sugars.
Roll balls in sugar while still hot.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: home-style scalloped potatoes
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper until blended.
Gradually add milk. Bring to a boil, cook and stir for 2 minutes or until sauce is thickened.
Place half of potatoes in greased 3 qt baking dish. Pour half of sauce over potatoes.
Repeat layers. Bake uncovered in 350 degree oven for 60 to 70 minutes or until potatoes are tender and top is lightly browned.
Serve immediately.
8 servings.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Combine eggs, juice from the can of pineapple, flour and butter and mix well.
Cook in double boiler.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Set aside and chill.

title: fried rice
directions: Combine onion and margarine in a 2-quart casserole. Microwave at High until onion is tender 1 1/2 to 5 minutes; set aside.
Stir bouillon into hot water until dissolved.
Add bouillon mixture, rice and green onions to casserole.
Cover and microwave at High until mixture boils, 6 1/2 to 13 minutes.
Let stand covered until liquid is absorbed 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in eggs and soy sauce.
Microwave uncovered at High 3 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes.
Fluff with a fork before serving.

title: low-fat biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients well and roll out on lightly floured board. Cut out biscuits.
Bake in 500° oven for 15 minutes.
Some ovens may vary on time.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt with pastry blender.
Mix egg, water and vinegar together and add to flour mixture.
Mix together to form a ball and roll out.
Makes two 9-inch double crusts.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine.
Add 1/4 to 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: oysters bienville
directions: Place oysters on the half shell in baking pan which has been filled with ice cream salt.
Partially bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Saute shallots, garlic and parsley in butter until brown.
Add flour and brown on low heat.
Add shrimp and mushrooms.
Slowly add the cream and wine.
Season to taste.
Add lemon juice and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour sauce over oysters, cover with mixture of bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Return to oven and brown approximately 10 to 12 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Place in loaf pan and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: banana pineapple nut bread
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together (except nuts).
Mix and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.
Makes 3 small or 2 large loaves.

title: chicken in foil on the grill
directions: Make 4 packages.
Lay piece of chicken on foil; season with paprika and garlic salt.
Bring four corners of foil together and set on grill, about 4 inches above coals.
Cook until chicken is half cooked.
Divide vegetables and add to chicken.
Pour soup over top and reseal foil.
Return to grill.
Cook until chicken is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Cook sausage on top of stove and drain.
Combine in casserole dish.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Coat chocolate chips and pecans in a spoon or so of the dry cake mix.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Fold in chocolate chip mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done in greased and floured tube pan.
Can serve with a scoop of ice cream and hot fudge or caramel ice cream topping.

title: billie's fruit bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, melted oleo and 2 eggs.
Press into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs.
Pour over top of first layer.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Freezes well.

title: savory party bread
directions: Cut bread lengthwise and crosswise without cutting through the bottom crust. Insert cheese between cuts. Combine butter, onions and poppy seeds. Drizzle over bread. Wrap in foil and place on a baking sheet. Bake at 350 degrees foor 15 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer or until cheese melts. Serves about 8.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of mixer until well blended.
Beat egg into mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix into mixture just until blended.
Stir into chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by tablespoons of dough 3 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake one baking sheet at a time at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: italian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in bag; place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add spaghetti sauce to bag.
Squeeze bag to blend.
Add chicken and green pepper to bag.
Turn bag to coat chicken.
Arrange chicken in even layers.
Close with nylon tie. Cut 6
(1/2-inch) slits in top of bag.
Bake until tender, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: grilled oriental chicken
directions: Wash chicken; set aside.
Place peppercorns in a blender and process for several seconds.
Add soy sauce, sherry and garlic. Pour marinade over chicken and let stand refrigerated for several hours, turning occasionally.
Cook chicken pieces over hot coals on a grill or smoker (12 to 15 minutes on a grill or 30 to 40 minutes in a smoker).
Turn pieces several times while cooking.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix crushed cookies with melted butter.
Press into freezer-proof bowl or container.
Spread vanilla ice cream over top of cookies.
Pour fudge topping in even layer over ice cream. Spread whipped topping over fudge.
Decorate top as desired.
Put in freezer for 2 hours.

title: crock-pot soup
directions: Brown the ground beef with the onion.
Put in crock-pot and add the remaining ingredients. Simmer all day.

title: taco dip
directions: Place vegetables on top of taco mixture.
Chill and serve with nacho chips.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Dip chicken in mixture of flour, salt and pepper. Brown in 2 tablespoons hot oil on top of stove. Remove chicken and place in a Pyrex dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with almonds.

title: jalapeno black-eyed pea and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add ground beef and brown.
Stir in jalapeno black-eyed peas, rice and tomatoes.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serves 6 to 8.

title: arkansas fried okra
directions: Put the first 5 of these ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, corn meal and flour; mix well.
In cast-iron skillet, heat shortening.
Pour okra mixture into hot grease.
Cover and cook on medium heat until tender.
Stir at intervals to avoid sticking and burning.
Serve hot.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Add salt to cabbage and let stand one hour. Squeeze out cabbage and add carrots and green peppers.
Make a syrup of vinegar, sugar, water, celery seed and mustard seed.
Mix and boil 1 minute.
Cool to lukewarm and pour over cabbage mixture. Freeze.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box and mix pudding mix as directed. Crumble one half cake in punch bowl.
Layer pudding mix, drained pineapple, cherry pie filling, Cool Whip, coconut and pecans. Start over, layering again.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: frog legs with sauce
directions: Dip frog legs in milk, then dip in flour.
Brown frog legs in skillet in butter (melted), for 10 to 15 minutes.
If legs are large, cook covered 15 minutes longer.
Remove to warm platter. Season with salt and pepper.
Add 1/4 cup each butter and almonds to skillet.
Brown lightly.
Add lemon juice.
Pour over legs, top with snipped parsley.
Serves 6.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring water to a boil; add sugar and syrup until dissolved and boil until spins a thread.
Add peanuts and cook slowly until golden brown.
Remove from heat; add butter, soda and vanilla. Stir quickly and spread on buttered cookie sheet.
Put in cool place to set.
When cool, break into small pieces.

title: linguine tuna salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine ReaLemon brand, oil, onion and seasonings.
Mix well.
Add hot linguine; toss.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: hot 'n spicy shrimp artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and dice.
Add shrimp, cream cheese, mayonnaise, picante sauce and Parmesan.
Mix well.
Spoon into 9-inch round Pyrex pie plate or Pyrex baking dish.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.
Can garnish with red pepper and green onion tops, if desired.
Serve with chips, vegetable dippers or Tostitos.
Best with Tostitos.

title: crockery barbecue beef
directions: In bowl, combine cola, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, garlic, bouillon, mustard, chili powder and red pepper.
Trim fat, cut meat into cubes for 3 1/2 to 4 quart slow cooker.
Put meat, onions with liquid; save about 1/2 cup to make sauce later.
Cook 10 to 12 hours slow or 5 to 6 hours on high.
Transfer meat to board and shred.
With saved liquid, mix ketchup and margarine. Drain cooking juices.
Mix meat with new juices, ketchup and margarine.
Heat, serve.

title: energy bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients on low heat, then add the remaining ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Set 1 hour. That's it!
Let's eat!

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and baking soda, then add Crisco. Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to flour mixture along with the buttermilk.
Roll out and place on greased baking pan and let rise a few minutes, then bake in a 350° oven until brown.
This makes a lot of biscuits, so what dough you do not use can be stored in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to two weeks.
If stored in the refrigerator, let set a few minutes after rolling out.
These freeze well after baking.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine spices, vinegar, oil and dressing in a saucepan. Bring to a full boil.
Pour immediately over washed mushrooms. Marinate at least 3 hours in closed container in refrigerator. Drain and serve as hors d'oeuvres.

title: smoked wild duck with sweet sauce
directions: Mix marinade by combining juice, brown sugar and liquid smoke. Add ducks and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Remove to let ducks come to room temperature.
Prepare charcoal smoker to manufacturer's instructions.
When coals ash over, liberally distribute hickory chunks over coals.
Fill drip pan with water and put ducks on smoker; cook 1 1/2 hours per pound.
Remove ducks. Take 1 cup of marinade, 1/3 cup liquid from drip pan and 1/2 teaspoon cornstarch and put in saucepan.
Simmer until thickens and use as a dipping sauce for ducks.

title: grape juice
directions: Boil grapes and water hard.
Don't mash. Cool and then strain.
For 1/2 gallon juice add 1 cup sugar.
Heat juice and sugar and cool.
Then put in jars.
Process in pan of water in oven on warm or on top of stove for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Beat eggs.
Add to melted margarine and sugar.
Mix in vanilla; add nuts.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and put in a greased casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter, stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to boil stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Gradually, pour over popped corn, mix well.
Turn into 2 large shallow baking pans. Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
After cooling, break apart.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt and peanut butter; mix well. Gradually add the sugars and cream well.
Add eggs and milk; mix well.
Sift together the flour and soda; blend with first mixture. Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: italian muffins
directions: Mix dry and wet ingredients separately.
Then combine until moistened evenly.
Add Mozzarella cheese last.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400°
for 20 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix powdered sugar, butter and peanut butter well with mixer. Roll in small balls.
Chill.
Melt chocolate bar and add paraffin. Melt and stir together.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture and place on wax paper until set.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and oil.
Add pumpkin.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add alternately with water to pumpkin mixture; mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Blend flour, salt and Crisco with pastry blender.
Mix cold water, vinegar and egg together, then add to first mixture until it forms a ball.
Will make 3 (9-inch) pie crusts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes in buttered casserole dish.
Crumble potato chips on top and brown.

title: sean's sugar delights
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake 12 minutes at 350° on a greased cookie sheet.

title: christmas rocks
directions: Cut fruit and chop nuts into small pieces.
Mix dry ingredients.
Work dry ingredient mixture in with the fruits and nuts.
Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Mix with the floured fruit. Dissolve the soda in 2 tablespoons of hot water.
Add this solution to the other ingredients.
Mix by hand.
Spoon onto cookie sheet. Bake 5 to 8 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt, flour and butter; mix well.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla, blending thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: homemade sausage
directions: Mix all
ingredients.
Divide
mixture in half, rolling into two loaves.
Wrap
each
loaf
in
foil,
shiny side out. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Poke
holes in foil and bake on broiler pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sandwich in a bun
directions: Mix all together and pile in doggie buns.
Wrap in foil and bake 5
to 10 minutes at 450°.
Makes approximately 1 dozen.

title: melted cheese pocket puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles.
Place 1 square cube of cheese on wide end and roll up, covering cheese completely.
Seal well.
Combine sesame seed and Parmesan cheese.
Dip rolls into the Italian dressing, then dip into the seed cheese mixture.
Place in ungreased muffin tins. Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from the oven and serve.
Refrigerate any leftovers (if you have any).

title: 2-2-1 salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions on box.
Add apricot nectar and pineapple; refrigerate.
To serve, top with cottage cheese.

title: quick chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix well and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: texas matador
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain. Brown beef.
Add salt, sugar and pepper in skillet.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce and garlic.
Cook for 10 minutes over low heat.
Add noodles, sour cream, cream cheese and onions.
Stir well.

title: baked fried chicken batter
directions: Batter chicken and bake at 325 degrees.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Pour into pan, then place rest of crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Place in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours.

title: pineapple delight cake
directions: Prepare and bake 2- or 9-inch layers from cake mix according to package directions; cool.
Stir pudding mix into crushed pineapple.
Prepare dessert topping according to package directions; fold in pineapple mixture.
Spread about 1-1/2 c. frosting on bottom cake layer; top with second layer.
Frost sides of cake lightly;
top cake with remaining frosting.
Garnish with halved pineapple slices and maraschino cherries.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix everything, except whites, together.
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Fold into mixture.
Pour into round spring pan. Bake for 1 hour.
Shut off oven and leave in oven for 1 hour with door ajar.

title: green pea salad
directions: Drain peas and other ingredients.
Mix lightly and refrigerate.
Serves 4.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients until just smooth.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 9-inch or 7 x 11-inch pan and bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until done.

title: barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add chuck roast.
Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 5 hours.
Tear meat apart and fill buns.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Mix together gelatin, pecans, coconut, condensed milk and vanilla.
Shape mixture into strawberries; chill at least 1 hour. Roll chilled berries into sugar crystals.
Add food coloring to almonds to tint a delicate green.
Use for leaves and stems of berries.
Store in a cool place.
Makes about 48 strawberries, depending on size.
They are real pretty, so tasty and decorative for a party.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together first 7 ingredients.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon 2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: creamy tuna twist
directions: In large bowl stir together first 3 ingredients until smooth. Add remaining ingredients.
Toss to coat well.
Cover, chill. Makes 4 servings.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust. Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with desired amount of pie filling.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Place in large dish the carrots, onions and green pepper in layers.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over carrots.
Cover tightly and place in refrigerator. Let stand 12 hours before serving.
Drain part of dressing from vegetables.
This can be used as a salad dressing for tossed salad.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, margarine, pecans and 1 egg.
Press mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 remaining eggs.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool before cutting. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: microwave meat and potato dish
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Add rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Microwave about 14 to 16 minutes.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 5 minutes more.

title: aunt margaret's sugar cookies
directions: Beat ingredients except flour together.
Add flour, gradually, and blend well.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Roll in 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass or fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 80 cookies.

title: turkey crush
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Blend on high speed until smooth.
An electric mixer can be used instead of blender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lasagne toss
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni shells according to directions on package for 7 minutes; drain.

title: light wheat rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl; add sugar and salt to the yeast mixture.
Melt 1/4 cup butter; cool to lukewarm.
Add butter, egg and whole wheat flour to yeast mixture, stirring well.
Gradually stir in enough all-purpose flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a well floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes).
Place in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down; cover and let rise in a warm place (85°) until doubled in bulk.

title: caramel-pecan sauce
directions: In a heavy saucepan combine sugar, brown sugar, light cream and margarine.
Cook over medium-high heat until boiling, stirring constantly to dissolve the sugars.
Reduce heat.
Cook and stir for 5 minutes more or until slightly thickened.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, salt and soda and blend well.
Add oatmeal, nuts and coconut.
Chill 2 hours.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Place all ingredients into a stockpot.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down heat to low and let simmer 2 to 4 hours, stirring frequently. Add water if you like your soup thinner.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels with milk in top of double boiler (do this before mixing cake as it will take a while to unwrap and melt caramels).
Combine cake mix with water, butter and eggs in large mixer bowl.
Blend on low speed for 30 seconds, then beat at medium speed 2 minutes.

title: big parker house rolls
directions: In bowl, mix yeast and water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in sugar, oil and egg.
Beat in 1 cup of flour.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured board and knead until smooth.
Roll dough into a 7-inch round.
Fold in half just off center and place on a baking sheet.
Let stand 25 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Combine melted margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; mix well.
Add coconut and drained pineapple.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Cook in a 325° to 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rockdale clam chowder
directions: Mix all ingredients into a large stock pot.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat.
Simmer for an additional 45 minutes.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Stew raisins with 2 cups water 20 minutes.
Add Crisco, cold water and 2 cups of sugar.
Add remaining ingredients except flour.
Beat in flour.
Bake in tube pan about 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown the chicken in the oil.
Remove chicken and cook the onions and garlic until tender, but not brown.
Return chicken to pot.
Combine tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, oregano, celery seed and bay leaves.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook, uncovered, 15 minutes longer, or until chicken is tender, turning occasionally.
Remove bay leaves and skim off fat.
Serve.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt oleo.
Add powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Pat into 8 x 8-inch pan and refrigerate.
Melt chocolate chips and pour on top.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Bring 2 cups water to boil.
Add Jell-O.
Dissolve.
Add strawberries and pineapple with their juices.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into glass dish. Let congeal.
Spread sour cream over Jell-O. Pour remaining Jell-O on top and congeal.

title: roma asparagus-tomato salad
directions: Slightly overlap lettuce leaves on chilled salad plate. Build salad in layers in order ingredients are given.
Dress just before serving.
May garnish with a few pitted black olives.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Beat eggs in small bowl. Add a dash of milk. Mix flour and Parmesan cheese in another bowl. Preheat oven to 350°; melt butter in casserole dish. Pour butter out of casserole dish. Dip chicken in egg mixture, then in cheese mixture.
Place in casserole. After all chicken has been coated, drizzle the melted butter over top of chicken. Bake about 45 minutes until chicken is lightly browned on top.

title: cranberry orange bubble loaf
directions: Divide	biscuit
dough	into
16 pieces.
Cut cranberry sauce into
pieces.
Shape each piece of dough around each piece of sauce.
Roll
balls
in melted butter, then in brown sugar.
Put in layers in a greased loaf pan (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch). Sprinkle
in nuts, if desired.
Pour any remaining butter and sugar over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, then turn out on plate.

title: chili
directions: Put all ingredients in a pot. Bring to a boil. Turn heat down and simmer 1 hour, stirring every 10 to 15 minutes. Freezes well for once-a-month cooking plan.

title: lazy housewife pickles
directions: Mix and set in refrigerator overnight, ready to eat.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and fry or broil as you would hamburgers.
Spray frypan or broiler pan with Pam.
Fry or broil for 5 minutes.
If you do not like well done, decrease cooking time.

title: sweet potato rolls
directions: Sift dry ingredients and work in shortening.
Put in sweet potatoes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 10 minutes at 450 degrees.
Can be frozen.

title: "oh boy" plus waffles
directions: Beat egg whites first. Preheat waffle iron. Oil with spray oil before using for each waffle. Sift together all dry ingredients. Combine remaining ingredients. Add just before baking.
Stir in egg whites to make batter fluffy. (Batter is thin.) Makes 10 or 12.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, egg and flour together until crumbly.
Spread over sliced peaches, with some of the juice removed, in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: maple pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs well, then beat in sugar, spices and salt.
Add maple syrup, evaporated milk and pumpkin, beating with rotary beater.
Pour into pastry-lined pan and bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 minutes longer or until a knife blade comes out cleanly when inserted near center.
Serve cold or slightly warm.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Arrange green beans in bundles of 8, wrapping 1/2 slice bacon around each.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours. Bake 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered, at 350° turning beans after first 20 minutes of baking. Remove beans from baking dish with slotted spoon.
Garnish bean bundles with strips of pimento before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Mix in buttermilk.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased pan.

title: martha's company casserole
directions: Cook noodles and make bottom layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown beef, add puree and seasonings.
Melt cheese and add to onion and pepper.
Spread cheese layer over noodles.
Spread beef mixture over cheeses.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients (except noodles) and put in casserole. Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Add noodles and bake 5 more minutes.

title: enchilada sauce
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add flour and stir until mixture is smooth.
Add all other ingredients and cook until tender.

title: taco salad
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put 2 1/2-quart ovenproof bowls upside down on a cookie sheet and place tortilla on each.
Bake 14 to 16 minutes, until lightly browned and crisp.
Lift off bowls and let cool on wire rack.
Bake remaining tortillas.

title: roasted potato salad
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place potatoes on a greased baking pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes, stirring once.
Mix dressing, bacon, eggs, onion, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Add potatoes; mix lightly. Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken and rice pilaf *
directions: In a 3/4-quart casserole dish, combine all ingredients, except chicken, butter and seasoning.
In a frying pan, melt butter, add seasonings and chicken.
Brown chicken a little.
Place on top of rice mixture in casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours, best if overnight.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine flour, oats, soda, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
Cream butter, add sugars gradually beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix.
Alternate dry ingredients and pumpkin.
Add chips, nuts or raisins.
Drop by 1/4 cup dough on lightly greased cookie sheet; spread out into a pumpkin shape.
Add a bit more dough for stem.
Bake until set and lightly browned.
Remove and cool on racks.
Decorate with icing, candies, etc.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 32 large cookies.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix together hamburger, onion, olives, chilies and soup. Layer in pan tortillas, enchilada sauce, meat and cheese.
Should layer about 2 or 3 times.
Use flat cake pan.
Bake at 400° until bubbly on top, about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fried eggplant(mock salmon patties)
directions: Boil eggplant until done (soft).
Remove from water; peel and mash pulp.
Add eggs, chopped onion, salt and pepper.
Add flour. Drop by tablespoon in medium-hot oil.
Fry until brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: marinade for chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate chicken overnight in refrigerator.
Cook approximately 2 hours on grill basting with marinade.
Before taking the chicken from the grill, brush with melted butter.

title: onion spread on toast
directions: Toast bread.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Cut bread into quarters.
Spoon mixture onto toast and put under broiler until golden.
Serve warm.

title: crazy cake
directions: Put all dry ingredients in bowl.
Make a hole in the middle and add all liquids.
Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Empty peaches
and
juice
in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Mix oleo, sugar, flour and egg.
Mix well and pour over fruit. Bake at 375°
for
minutes
or golden brown.
Also may use frozen fruit but
sugar the fruit and spoon on the mixture and bake as directed.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: Mix all ingredients together except tortillas and 1/2 the cheese.
Place 3 tablespoons of mix on each tortilla.
Roll up and place on a greased baking dish.
Pour the rest of mixture over tortillas.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: five layer pudding
directions: Mix flour, oleo and nuts together and form a crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool thoroughly.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar and fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on the crust.

title: baked sliced potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Place overlapping in buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients. Brush slices with mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix together pork and beans, salt, barbecue sauce and brown sugar; add browned meat to beans.
Place mixture in casserole.
Cover casserole with can Hungry Jack flaky biscuits.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over biscuits.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: cranberry walnut swirls
directions: Pastry:
In large bowl combine butter, sugar, egg and vanilla. Beat until fluffy.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture and mix just until combined.
Wrap and refrigerate dough 1 hour.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender. Pour stock into separate bowl; remove bones and tear meat into medium size pieces. Add margarine to package of dressing. In another bowl, mix sour cream, mushrooms, water chestnuts and celery soup. In baking dish, layer 1/2 of dressing. Place chicken pieces on top of dressing; place sour cream mixture layer, then rest of dressing. Pour 2 cups of chicken stock or enough to make mixture moist. Bake at 250° until hot and bubbly.

title: paczki
directions: Spread peanut butter between Ritz crackers.
Dip in melted semi-sweet or milk chocolate (dipping) candy.
Let excess drip off. Place on wax paper to let chocolate dry.

title: ida's scalloped corn
directions: Mix above ingredients together and put in a medium baking dish.
Bake in a 300 degree oven for 30 minutes.
Then add grated cheese over the top when done.
8 servings.

title: pizza bites
directions: Mix margarine and garlic; spread on muffin halves.
Cut each muffin half into 4 wedges, don't separate.
Place 1 slice of pepperoni and 1 tomato half on each muffin wedge.
Place in broiler pan.
Mix cheese and oregano.
Sprinkle over muffins.
Set oven to broil or 550°.
Broil with the tops 5 inches from heat until cheese melts, about 2 minutes.
Cut to separate wedges. Serves 6 at 65 calories each.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies in food processor or blender.
Mix pudding and milk; add Cool Whip.
Layer part of Oreos in bottom of flowerpot.
Add part of pudding; repeat, ending with Oreos on top. Add a silk flower and serve with a garden shovel.
You may also add gummy worms.

title: cheddarburger skillet
directions: In a skillet, brown the beef and onion.
Pour off fat.
Stir in soups and water; add potatoes.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Mix with hands (does better).
Mix Crisco and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add sifted flour and salt.
Add vanilla and lemon. In separate bowl add buttermilk, soda and water, then add to other blended ingredients.
Flour or sugar well-greased Bundt pan (Crisco or margarine).
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Preheat oven. Test.

title: pot roast meat loaf
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients; shape into loaf.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick; place on both sides of meat.
Quarter onions and cut up carrots.
Place over potatoes.
Mix parsley leaves, salt and pepper; sprinkle over everything.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: apple biscuits
directions: Cut apples in 1/4's and wrap in biscuits.
Put in dish, seams down.
Press flat.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Take out of oven; turn biscuits over.
In separate pan, bring to a boil sugar, water, margarine and cinnamon.
Pour over biscuits and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Bake cake and cool. Mix 1/2 cup sugar, coconut milk (all) and 1/2 cup coconut.
Put on top of first layer of cake.
Mix vanilla, whipping cream, and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cover whole cake, then sprinkle with coconut. Serve immediately or refrigerate.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Heat in top of double boiler the caramels and milk.
Stir. Pour over ice cream.

title: chewy bars
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine, 1 egg and cake mix thoroughly and press into a grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix 8 ounce cream cheese, 1 box powdered sugar, and 2 eggs and beat for 5 minutes.
Pour over top of first layer.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool in refrigerator before cutting in two squares.

title: mexican salad
directions: Bake cornbread and drain beans.
Mix tomatoes, bell peppers and green onions.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soup, onion, celery, rice, mayonnaise and broth.
Mix well and place in casserole dish.
Mix Rice Krispies and butter and put on top of casserole.
Bake on 350° for 35 minutes.

title: quiche a la barker
directions: *Frozen or fresh but precooked asparagus, diced or sliced fresh mushrooms, cut broccoli or diced ham, or a combination of these vegetables.

title: honey-apple pancakes
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, salt, apple pie spice and baking soda.
In a small bowl beat egg slightly; stir in apple juice, honey and oil.
Add egg mixture all at once to flour mixture; stir until blended but still slightly lumpy.
For each pancake, pour about 1/4 cup of batter onto a hot, lightly greased griddle or heavy skillet.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes or until pancakes have a bubbly surface and slightly dry edges. Turn and cook for 2 to 3 minutes more or until golden brown. Makes about eight 4-inch pancakes.
Each pancake has 124 calories and 3 grams of fat.
These make for a great lo-cal breakfast!

title: best pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together. Bake until a knife inserted 1 inch from side comes out clean. The center may still look soft but will set later. Bake at 425° for 45 to 55 minutes in a 9 inch pie shell.

title: quick and easy pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place biscuits in ungreased 8 or 9-inch round cake pan; press over bottom and about 1-inch up sides to make crust.
Melt margarine in saucepan; add pie filling, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.
Serves 5.

title: mom's chili sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes and grind.
Also onions and peppers.
Combine ingredients and cook until the mixture is thick (about 3 hours). The sugar should be added after it starts to thicken.
Stir often so it doesn't stick.
Seal in jars.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: fudgies
directions: In large bowl, mix as listed.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan lightly greased and floured.
Sprinkle 1 cup chocolate chips over the batter.
Over chocolate chips put 1 cup nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt peanut butter and chips in saucpan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Pour over Rice Krispies and mix.
Put half of mixture into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Press and pack it down. Chill in refrigerator while you continue on.

title: crusty beef, cheese and noodle casserole
directions: Heat oil.
Add onion and cook until soft.
Add meat and cook until meat loses red color.
Add sauce and salt.
Arrange in casserole half of noodles, half of sauce and half of cheese.
Make another layer of each topping with cheese.	Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Top should be brown.
Makes 8 to 10 big servings.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Saute onions in margarine.
Boil celery in water.
Combine all ingredients (except the kidney beans).
Simmer 2 hours.
Add beans and simmer another 1/2 hour.

title: salsa
directions: Put whole tomatoes in pot of boiling water for about 2 minutes, then put into cool water.
This makes it easy to remove skins.
In a large pot, bring all ingredients to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 1 to 3 hours or until desired thickness, stirring often.
Pour into pint jars, then process in water bath for about 4 to 5 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 pints.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fill large pot with hot water and lightly salt. Bring water to a boil.
Wash potato skins under cool water with veggie brush. Place whole potatoes in water.
Boil until tender. Drain off hot water and run cold water over potatoes.
When potatoes are cool enough to handle, peel
skin off under slow running cool water. Dice potato and place in bowl.
Finely chop onion and add to potatoes.
Add salt, pepper, garlic powder, vegetable oil, vinegar and mix well.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: In
a
large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients except kisses.
Blend
well
at low speed.
Shape into balls, using a rounded
teaspoon.	Roll
balls
in
sugar; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Immediately top with candy kisses and press down firmly.

title: sausage cheese bread
directions: Cook sausage and onion over low heat until meat is browned, then drain.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl and add to other. Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.
Serve with jalapeno jelly if you wish.

title: sausages in barbecue sauce
directions: Slice sausage across the link in slices 1/4-inch.
Put in casserole dish and cover with barbecue sauce.
Microwave about 5 minutes or until hot and bubbly, stirring about halfway through time.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, butter and eggs.
Add the flour, cocoa, dash of salt, pecans and vanilla.
Mix well. Bake in an oblong pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from the oven and place the marshmallows on top. Put back in the oven to melt the marshmallows.
Cool and top with icing.

title: seven-up layer cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Mix well.
Reserve 2/3 cup of batter to use in frosting.
Bake in oblong cake pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cranberry bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together the flour, oats, brown sugar, lemon peel and baking soda.
Stir in the margarine and mix thoroughly.
Reserve 1 cup of the flour-oat mixture for the topping.
Pat the remaining oat mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: giant popovers
directions: Grease 2 popover pans.
Each pan holds six 5-ounce cups.
In a large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat eggs until frothy.
Beat in milk and butter.
At low speed, beat flour and salt into egg, milk and butter mixture.
Fill cups until half filled.
Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.
Make slit in each popover to let steam out. Bake 5 minutes more.
Remove popovers from pans immediately.

title: filet of sole with cheese sauce
directions: Thaw lobster tails by separating them and setting out (room temperature) for approximately 4 hours.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, cream of tartar and soda; add to creamed mixture, beating well.
Stir in vanilla.
Chill dough 2 hours.
Work with half of dough at a time.
Store remainder in refrigerator.
Roll dough on lightly floured board to 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 425 degrees for 6 - 8 minutes or until lightly browned. Frost with decorator frosting.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: banana chips
directions: Mix sugar and salt together in a bowl.
In another bowl, add 3 tablespoons sugar and salt mixture to every 3 cups of sliced bananas.
Mix well and deep fry, a few at a time, until golden. Remove, separate sticking pieces and cool.

title: beef tenderloin with horseradish sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Rub tenderloin with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Place tenderloin on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 500° for 5 minutes per pound of tenderloin.
Do not open oven during cooking process.
After appropriate baking time, turn oven off (still do not open oven door) and let tenderloin remain in oven for 35 minutes.
Then remove, let cool slightly and slice.
Mix horseradish and sour cream to serve with the tenderloin.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water, cranberry sauce and partially set
jello.
Then
stir
in sour cream and let set. Make in 9-inch square container.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt last four ingredients.
Cut biscuits in half, then cut the half in thirds.
Then shake in a bag with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and pour melted mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: white house pecan pie
directions: Add sugar, syrup, salt and vanilla to butter and beat with a sturdy hand mixer until thoroughly blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat gently just until blended.
Fold in the pecans and bake in moderate oven at 375° on rack directly below center (not on bottom) until top is toasted brown and filling is set to soft pudding stage, about 40 to 50 minutes.
If top gets too dark, toward end, place foil tent over or turn oven temperature down. Cool on wire rack.

title: rhubarb bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together the rhubarb, sugar and water.
Place in small greased baking dish.
Pinch rolls apart. Arrange across top of mixture to form top crust.
Pour melted margarine over crust.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: fruit and cheese pizza(yield: 8-12 slices)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 375°.

title: cucumber-chili salad
directions: Mix salt, vinegar, sugar and chili pepper in bowl; add cucumber.
Gently toss to coat cucumbers.
Serve at once.
Yields 4 servings.

title: triple chocolate brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch pie plate.
In a small mixer bowl, beat eggs; blend in sugar and butter.
In a separate bowl, stir together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to egg mixture, beating until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla. Spread batter into prepared pie plate.
Bake 35 minutes or until set (pie will not test done in center).
Cool completely; cut into wedges.
Serve with ice cream; top with chocolate topping.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix and cook to soft ball stage (sugar, butter and milk). Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme. Stir until partially cool.
Put in a greased 6 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: bubbles
directions: Mix and let sit overnight if you can.
This will give them time to work and will make bigger bubbles.
Recipe may be adjusted to make large quantities.
Glycerine is available at most drug stores.

title: piquant sauce for fish
directions: Combine all ingredients in the order given, beating after each addition until blended.
No cooking is necessary.
Pour over any fish just before serving.
Makes 1 cup.

title: dog bones(not for humans)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix all ingredients until well blended. Knead dough 2 minutes.
Roll on floured surface to 1/4-inch and cut.
Bake 30 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: pastry
directions: Cut shortening into flour and sugar.
Beat egg.
Mix vinegar with enough water to make 3/4 cup of liquid and add this to flour mixture.
This recipe makes 4 or 5 pastry shells.
These may be frozen.

title: summer sausage
directions: Combine ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Divide into 4 equal parts.
Shape into a long thin log.
Wrap each in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Unwrap and place in broiler pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Refrigerate until needed.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together softened cream cheese, sugar, peanut butter and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell.
Keep in refrigerator or may be made ahead and frozen.

title: cpk chopped bbq chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat
and
garlic.
Drain fat.
Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper
and
oregano.
Cover;
simmer
30 to 45 minutes. Cook noodles according to package directions.
Layer noodles, sauce, cottage
cheese
and cheese mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry hamburger and onions and cook rice.
Mix remaining ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Mix together.
Pour over pork chops or chicken. Bake in oven at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or put in crock-pot on low for 6 to 7 hours. Mixture is enough for 4 to 6 pork chops and enough for 1 chicken.
Good with mashed potatoes.
Will be enough sauce for gravy.

title: chocolate italian cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Add pecans, sour cream and coconut.
Bake in three 9-inch cake pans.
Bake as directed on box.
Cool cake completely and frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: easy cheesy lemon bars
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Mix with fork until moist.
Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan, greased on bottom only.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bone chicken; place in baking dish. Mix sour cream and soup. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle cracker crumbs, mixed with poppy seed, over mixture. Pour melted margarine over crumbs. Bake until bubbly at 450°, about 30 minutes.

title: marinade for fish
directions: Stir together oil, soy sauce, lemon juice, lemon peel and garlic.
Pour over fish.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours. Remove fish from marinade and cook over medium-hot charcoal or under a preheated broiler.

title: sweet corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add cream, egg and vinegar; beat.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Stir flour and baking powder 3 times.
Cream butter and sugar. Add flour and baking powder alternately with diluted milk.
Add vanilla and stir until smooth.
Add eggs.
Bake in muffin pan or in shallow pan at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into squares or fancy shapes.
Makes 20 tea cakes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Place rhubarb in cake pan (greased), 9 x 13-inch.
Sprinkle with jello and sugar.
Let stand 1 hour.
Sprinkle marshmallows over all.
Mix as directed the cake mix.
Pour over marshmallows. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: orange-glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Allow potatoes to cool to touch; peel and slice. Arrange slices in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Combine the remaining ingredients in a small saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Pour glaze over sweet potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 5 to 6 servings.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Beat eggs and milk together. Sift in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix. Roll out 1/8-inch thick on a lightly floured board. Cut into small squares. Deep fat fry at 380° until brown. Drain on absorbent paper.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add all other ingredients and mix with wooden spoon.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
This may be used for layer cake also.

title: glorified rice
directions: Prepare jello as usual.
Cool and whip.
Add sugar, salt, cold rice, marshmallows, whipped cream and pineapple.
Fold into jello and let set.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: In a bowl place a layer of cabbage and a layer of onion rings. Cover with 3/4 cup sugar.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except retain 1 cup of Cheddar cheese for topping. Put mixture into 9-inch baking dish. Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: deluxe meat loaf
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add onion and chopped meat; mix well.
Line a loaf pan (8 x 5 x 3-inch) with bacon across the width of pan.
Pack meat mixture into pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven.
Invert meat loaf on baking sheet; raise oven temperature to very hot (450°).
Return meat loaf to oven for about 10 minutes to crisp bacon.
Garnish with heated canned broiled mushrooms, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple squares
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Crumble raw hamburger into square dish.
Add cream of mushroom soup (undiluted).
Layer with onion or peas or peas and carrots (drained).
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Layer in pan in given order; cover and bake at 250° for 4 hours.

title: oyster stew
directions: Melt butter; add oysters and oyster liquid.
Simmer gently until edges begin to curl.
Scald milk and add to oysters.
Add salt and pepper.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: hawaiian dessert
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Make two 9 x 13-inch cakes. Cool.
Mix pudding, cream cheese, milk and extract.
Beat well. Stir in pineapple.
Spread on cooled cakes.
Top with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with coconut.
You can use Cool Whip instead of whipping cream.
May be frozen up to 1 month.

title: devil in disguise(corn bread)
directions: For best results, use a cast-iron skillet.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Prepare macaroni according to box directions and drain.
Blend together remaining ingredients and chill.
Serves 8.

title: apple squares
directions: Sift together into mixing bowl the flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in butter or margarine and grated lemon rind until particles are the size of peas.
Sprinkle milk over mixture, tossing lightly with fork until dough is moist and holds together.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out half the dough to 15 x 10-inches.
(Roll dough on wax paper.)
Turn over onto ungreased baking sheet.
Peel off wax paper and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange broccoli in greased casserole dish.
Mix soup, juice, mayonnaise and cheese.
Spoon over broccoli.
Top with pimentos, crumbs and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lizzies
directions: Cream sugar and butter well; add beaten eggs.
Sift together 1/2 cup flour, soda and spices; add to egg mixture.
Flour raisins with remaining flour (1 cup).
Add milk and bourbon, mixing well; add raisins, nuts, citron, candied cherries and pineapple.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until browned.
You may place a cherry on each as you drop them.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Combine, chill and serve.

title: sauce for ribs
directions: Slice onions over ribs.
Pour sauce over ribs.
Bake in 350° oven for 2 hours or until done.

title: egg drop noodle soup
directions: Place chicken stock in large saucepan and bring to boil.
Add noodles.
Boil 5 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Reduce heat to simmer; stir eggs, lemon juice, salt and pepper together well. Slowly add eggs to stock in thin streams.
Stir gently with fork. Simmer for 1 minute or until eggs have set.
Sprinkle soup with chopped scallions and serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: italian stuffed pasta shells
directions: Cook shells until done.
Pour marinara sauce into saucepan. Heat.
Cook spinach as directed and drain.
Mix with Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese and eggs in a large bowl.
Pour marinara sauce over all and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: layered salad
directions: Prepare salad.
Shred lettuce and place in bottom of large glass bowl.
Then layer green pepper, onion, celery and peas. Spread with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cut tomatoes into cubes and arrange on salad.
Pour on Italian dressing.
Fry bacon and crumble on top of tomatoes.
Garnish with boiled eggs and black olives.

title: super easy fruit cobbler
directions: In an oblong Pyrex dish, melt one stick of margarine.
In a mixing bowl, combine milk, sugar, vanilla and flour; mix well. Pour this in Pyrex dish on top of melted margarine and put fruit on top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: sweetheart fruit pie
directions: Stir cornstarch into cold water until thoroughly dissolved. Add this to fruit and apple juice concentrate.
Heat mixture over medium heat until thick.
Pour into crust and chill until firm.

title: rati mum's special chicken
directions: Heat oil and butter together and brown chicken.
On peeled, halved onion, stick the cloves and cinnamon.
Crush pepper pods and add along with onion to the chicken.
Add garlic, slivered. Add tomato sauce can or blended fresh tomatoes and ketchup.
Add salt and green peppers.
When chicken is almost cooked, add boiled potatoes and serve with rice.

title: texas cow patties
directions: Roll out all of the crescent rolls together (like a pie crust).
Sprinkle with raw breakfast sausage.
Roll it up like a log.
Cut into circles about 1/2 inch thick.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 375° until brown.

title: spiced pineapple
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple chunks; mix with remaining ingredients.
Place in refrigerator; gently shake now and then. Enhances flavor after standing a day or two.
Excellent with ham or turkey dinners or as bite-sized hors d'oeuvres.
Yield: 2 to 3 cups.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning mix with sour cream.
Layer all ingredients in pan, beginning with refried beans, sour cream mixture, chiles, etc., in order
listed.
Bake or microwave until cheese melts and dip is heated through.

title: korff kids favorite cheese ball
directions: In large bowl soften cream cheese.
Add Worcestershire sauce, green onions, soup mix and half of beef.
Stir well.
Shape into ball and roll in other half of beef.
Place on plate and cover with plastic wrap.
Chill at least 3 hours or overnight.
Serve with Ritz.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Roll in balls.
Press with greased glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 375°.

title: tasty rice
directions: Put all ingredients in a casserole.
Bake uncovered about 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook fryers in enough water to cover chicken.
Cook onion, celery and bell pepper in oleo until soft and clear.
Add all of the cans of soup.
Cook spaghetti in water.
Cook chicken until done.

title: wild rice chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the chicken, rice, water chestnuts and green onions.

title: fluffy banana cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.

title: indian summer salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; add orange juice, pineapple and oranges.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: crusty pound cakes
directions: Mix and beat all ingredients together for exactly 11 minutes. Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: honey spice dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and serve with chicken nuggets.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook cream, sugar, margarine and salt to soft ball stage. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream; beat well.
Pour into buttered pan to cool.
Cut into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add broccoli, soup, milk, salt, pepper and Cheez Whiz.
Cook until cheese melts.
Then add rice. Place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into balls and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream
butter,	shortening and sugar.
Beat well.
Add 1 egg at	a time.
Add flour and 7-Up alternately.
Add flavoring and mix
well.	Grease	and flour cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or longer until done.

title: grandma's cupcakes
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Mix with mixer.
Stir in the chocolate chips.
Put liners in cupcake pans; fill 1/2 full with cake mix.
On top, add 1 spoon of mixture of cream cheese, sugar and egg.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until done.

title: spicy chile
directions: Brown meats separately and drain. Add peppers, onions, beans and tomato products (mash one can of beans before adding). Stir. Add seasonings.
Stir. Cook on low heat at least 1 hour, stirring occasionally. This is hot and not for the faint of heart!

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form in balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Mash with table fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Bake at 300° in 2 greased bread pans for 45 to 50 minutes, or at 325° in Bundt pan for 1 hour.
Remove from pan after 10 minutes and turn out onto powdered sugar covered wax paper.

title: gumbo jambalaya
directions: Combine all ingredients except shrimp in a 4-quart pot.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring often, until rice absorbs liquid.
During last 3 minutes of cooking, add shrimp.

title: scalloped scallops
directions: Butter an 8-inch baking casserole.
Wash scallops, cutting in half if very large.
Drain well.
Mix crumbs, crushed crackers and butter.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well and roll into small balls.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400° or until brown.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Roll hamburger into small balls.
Place in pot with diced onion and enough water to cover.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add cubed potatoes and carrots.
Cook for 1/2 hour or until carrots and potatoes are soft.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 5.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Add flour, soda and salt.
In a separate bowl mix eggs, jello, sugar, oil and buttermilk.
Add dry mixture to the egg mixture. Mix well.
Fold in frozen strawberries (thawed).
Grease and flour pans (Bundt or single pans).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.
Use Cool Whip or white icing.
Top with strawberries.

title: easy cajun shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Marinate for 30 minutes in refrigerator.
Then thread onto skewers and place on grill.
Brush with remaining marinade and rotate regularly until shrimp are pink (10 to 15 minutes).

title: frosted pecans
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and boil until thread forms.
Add the pecans and stir until coated.
Spread on waxed paper and separate when cool.

title: mister may's garbanzo bean salad
directions: *All peppers should be approximately the same size.

title: salmon egg loaf
directions: Prepare fish in fillets.
Salt and pepper fish and coat generously in corn bread.
Fry in a hot skillet of bacon grease until golden brown. While trout is frying prepare the Kamloop Sauce.

title: chicken rice bake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken. Pour in large baking dish. Lay chicken pieces on top of rice mixture.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lentil stew
directions: Saute celery, potato and carrot in oil.
Add lentils, water and tomato.
Bring to boil, then cover and simmer about 1 hour. (Check to be sure liquid hasn't boiled out.
Add more water if needed.)

title: crusty beef casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook ground beef, onion and garlic until beef is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off grease.
Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder, salt, pinto beans and corn.
Spoon beef mixture in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over meat mixture.
Prepare 1 (6 ounce) package corn bread mix according to package directions.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until corn bread is golden.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening, vanilla and sugar, add all other ingredients, except nuts, and mix until smooth.
Then stir in nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan 50 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Fry the extra lean ground beef until crumbly.
Add salt to taste.
Cool.
Make a salad of lettuce, tomatoes, onions and avocados.
Add kidney beans, ground beef, French dressing and 1/2 of the Doritos.
Toss.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Put jello in bowl.
Boil 2 cups of water.
Pour over jello. Mix well.
Stir in cans of blueberries and pineapple.
Set in refrigerator and chill until firm.
May set in freezer 30 minutes then set in refrigerator.
Mix sour cream, vanilla, cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Spread over top of firm mixture. Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Melt butter and stir in the Worcestershire sauce; pour over the dry mixture.
Bake at 200° for 2 hours.
Stir every 1/2 hour with a wooden spoon or some other spoon.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a Dutch oven or small soup pot, melt butter.
Saute onions 10 minutes, then cover and cook on low for 10 minutes.
Add broth and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Preheat broiler.
Place cheese on toast and broil until cheese is brown, about 3 minutes maximum. Serve with soup.
(You can also use small ovenproof soup bowls, place bread on top of soup, then the cheese and broil.
Fancy!)

title: fast and fabulous golden divan
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over high heat, heat water, onion and butter to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add stuffing; toss to mix well.
Spoon into 2-quart oblong baking dish.
Arrange broccoli and turkey/chicken over stuffing.
In medium bowl, combine soup, 1/2 cup cheese, milk and mushrooms.
Pour over broccoli and turkey/chicken.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese over soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Garnish with fresh sage and thyme.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Blend in mixer.
Pour in greased casserole dish.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Cream together with Marshmallow Creme and lemon peel.
Allow to set 10 minutes so lemon peel can soften in mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Dip fresh strawberries, bananas or grapes.
Can be used with any fresh fruit.

title: chicken salad
directions: Chop cooked chicken and add chopped celery. Add hard-boiled eggs. Blend in mayonnaise just before serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over hot water in top of double boiler.
Mix flour, sugar and salt, stir into chocolate, mixing until well blended.
Add 1 cup of the hot milk and stir until smooth.
Add remaining milk and continue to cook, stirring frequently until mixture is smooth and thickened (about 15 minutes).
Beat egg yolks well; stir in a little of the chocolate mixture, then pour back into rest of hot mixture and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla. Pour immediately into cooled pie shell.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then slowly beat in the 1/3 cup of sugar until very thick and smooth.
Pile lightly and quickly over pie filling so meringue touches edge of crust all around.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Bake in moderate oven 350°F 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool before cutting.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix all ingredients and form into 1-inch balls. Bake 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet until golden brown. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: apple strudel
directions: Beat
eggs
lightly,
add melted butter, water, vinegar and salt.
Then gradually add liquid mixture to flour.
Knead until dough
is
very
elastic
and
does
not stick to bowl. Divide into 5 balls, put in pan and cover with cloth.
Put in warm place and let stand about 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, prepare the filling. Core
and slice 18 apples (peeling optional) and add 3/4 cup
or more sugar for each strudel.
Add 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon for each strudel
(in
bowl
mix
sugar and cinnamon together).
Three cups filling
for 5 strudels.
Mix a little of each:
corn
flakes, vanilla
wafers
and graham crackers. Mix together 5 cups pecans (chopped small), 5 cups coconut and raisins (optional).

title: cheese and beef ball
