directions: Blend softened cream cheese with mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce.
Add parsley, onion and 4 ounces of beef.
Place on platter or in small dish; sprinkle remaining beef on top.
Serve with rye bread.
Serves 10 to 16.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a mixing bowl and beat for 3 minutes. Pour into a Bundt pan sprayed with cooking spray and floured. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean. Glaze.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Follow directions on cake box, then add the blackberries.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Put bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: candied pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
Spread pecans in single layer on jelly roll pan and roast 15-20 minutes.
DO NOT BURN!
Remove pecans and let cool.
Increase oven to 325 degrees.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gently fold in sugar, salt and cinnamon. Once pecans are cooled, gently fold into egg white mixture.
Melt butter in jelly roll pan and return pecans to pan in single layer. Bake 30 minutes, turning pecans every 10 minutes, until butter is gone.

title: orange julius
directions: Place ingredients in blender and blend together 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve in fancy glass.

title: zucchini surprise
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add zucchini; put lid on. Cook and stir until zucchini is almost tender.
Peel and chop tomato or tomatoes, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Simmer about 15 minutes.

title: sheet apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and egg until creamy.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Add gradually to creamed mixture and add milk.
Spread batter on a greased cookie sheet.
Slice apples and arrange over batter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, cinnamon and pats of butter or margarine.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: green chile enchiladas
directions: In
a
large saucepan mix cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soup,
1 can of water and the can of evaporated milk. Add a small amount of cheese and heat, stirring occasionally, until creamy.
If
the substance is too thick, add more water and/or milk. Add peppers.

title: meat loaf supreme (low-fat)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl, mix well and pack lightly in a meat loaf pan.
Coat top of meat loaf with barbecue sauce. Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Check after 1/2 hour.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, lemon peel, nutmeg and salt. Add berries and toss well.
Place in pie crusts, dot with butter and bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: glazed chicken breast
directions: Brush chicken pieces thoroughly with teriyaki base and glaze with honey and pineapple.
Cook chicken on grill 4 to 5 inches from hot coals 15 minutes or until tender, turning and brushing every 5 minutes with remaining baste and glaze.
(Or broil 5 inches from heat source about 15 minutes.
Turn and brush every 5 minutes with baste and glaze.)
Makes 6 servings.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Mix cooked spaghetti, egg, milk, garlic powder and 2 cups of the mozzarella cheese. Spread into a 9 x 13 pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Brown the hamburger and drain the fat.
Add spaghetti sauce and oregano.
Simmer a little.
Spread over the spaghetti.
Put slices of pepperoni all over the top.
Spread with remaining 1 1/2 cups of mozzarella cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° until bubbly.
Variation:
After you pour the spaghetti sauce mix over the spaghetti, you may freeze the dish and use later. When you pull it out of the freezer, top with pepperoni and cheese and bake.

title: hodgepodge bars
directions: Crush biscuits into shreds.
Spread in bottom of generously buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle coconut, chocolate and butterscotch morsels in layers over biscuits.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over all.
Scatter nuts on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Let cool in pan.
Cut into bars.

title: cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together flour, pumpkin, vanilla, salt and soda.
Combine remaining ingredients with dry mixture.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 350°.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Stir in liquids.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream. Refrigerate.

title: lumpy dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Chill for 24 hours.
Serve with thin wheat crackers.
Makes 15 servings.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, melted chocolate and vanilla.
Sift baking powder, salt and flour; add to mixture.
Mix in oats and pecans.
Drop by teaspoons on a greased cookie sheet. Press flat if desired and bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: prawns in tomato sauce
directions: With a kitchen scissor, snip the legs and tails of the prawns. Cut in 1-inch diagonal pieces.
Dredge in cornstarch and fry until crisp.
Set aside.
Saute the leeks and the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer until thick, then add fried prawns.
Simmer until sauce is almost dry.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas with baking soda in bowl.
Let stand for several minutes.
Combine shortening, sugar and egg in mixer bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Add banana mixture, flour and salt alternately, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in pecans.
Spoon into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: bacon salad dressing
directions: Fry bacon and drain most of fat off.
Mix all ingredients except vinegar, water and bacon.
Heat water and vinegar to boiling; stir in egg mixture.
Reduce heat and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add bacon.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomatoes and parsley.
Pour marinade over the tomatoes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Marinate in refrigerator 1 to 2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In large skillet melt butter and add celery and onion and saute, or in microwave melt butter, add celery and onion, cook until heated to either choice add soup and Cheese Whiz.
Stir until the cheese is melted.
Add chopped broccoli and stir. Prepare rice according to directions.
Spread evenly in 9 x 13 pan. Top with broccoli mixture.
Bake 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until it looks bubbly and done.
You can add more of each item to your taste.

title: orange marmalade
directions: Combine oranges, grapefruit and water in a large kettle.
Boil for 1 hour or until fruit is soft.
Add sugar and boil for 45 minutes.
Add lemon juice and boil until thick.
Pour into glasses and seal with paraffin.

title: peachtree ribs
directions: Place ribs in Dutch oven, cover with water, bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer until tender, 1 to 2 hours.
Drain meat and place in a glass 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine peaches, ketchup, vinegar, soy sauce, brown sugar, garlic and ginger; pour over meat.
Let marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Drain well, reserving marinade.

title: greek vegetable salad
directions: In large bowl, toss together lettuce, tomatoes, cucumber, onion and green pepper.
Top with cheese.
In a separate small bowl, whisk together oil, vinegar, water, garlic, oregano and black pepper.
Pour over salad and gently toss.
Serves 4.

title: mock cherry pie
directions: Place all ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Set aside and cool.
Place cooled ingredients in pie shell and bake in oven at 400° for 35 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
Ice cream enhances flavor.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in 7 1/2 x 12-inch flat dish sprayed with Pam. Add cheese and crumbs.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruited chicken
directions: Mix water, vinegar, molasses,
soy
sauce and pepper in 2-quart casserole.	Microwave on High
for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes. Stir after 45 seconds.
Cut
chicken
into strips and place in casserole and cover.
Refrigerate
for
hour.
Add
apples, walnuts and raisins.
Microwave until apples are tender.
Stir in oranges, cover and set
aside.
Mix juice and cornstarch in small mixing bowl.
Microwave until thickened, stirring 3 or 4 times. Pour over chicken and stir.
Serve over rice.

title: oven french fries
directions: Cut the potatoes into about 8 wedges and place on a cookie sheet.
Melt butter.
Brush onto cookie sheet, then use remaining on the potatoes.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Bake in 400° oven until golden brown and crispy (45 minutes).

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts flat and put in bottom of baking dish. Pour lemon juice over chicken.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix bread crumbs and cheese together.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Pour melted butter over bread crumbs and cheese mixture. Cook in oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Soak cracker crumbs in milk; add meat, eggs, onion and seasonings. Mix well. Shape in loaf in shallow baking pan or lightly pack into 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Garnish with pepper and onion rings. Yield: 8 servings.

title: coconut pan cake
directions: Bake cake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Punch holes in cake with fork.
While cake is still warm, pour mixture of cream of coconut and sweetened condensed milk over cake.
Spread Cool Whip over cake and top with coconut.
Chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Put cheeses in mixing bowl; let stand until soft.
Grind pecans and add to cheeses.
Add grated onion and a dash of pepper.
Work with hands to form a large ball; cover with parsley.
Chill and serve.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Boil Jell-O and pineapple (with juice) together.
Let cool, then add other ingredients.
Chill.

title: apple betty
directions: Spray 9 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish with cooking spray such as Pam.
Pour in pie filling; spread.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over filling.
Drizzle with melted oleo.
Bake at about 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brown.
Just before removing from oven, add topping of your choice.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: blueberry-yogurt breakfast shake
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Makes 1 shake.

title: pecan glazed pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven and a baking sheet to 375°.
In a large bowl, using a wire whisk, beat together eggs, pumpkin, evaporated milk, 3/4 cup brown sugar and pumpkin pie spice.
Place frozen pie crust on preheated baking sheet.
Pour filling in crust and bake for 40 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook meat and onion in a large skillet over medium heat until meat is browned and onion is tender; drain.
Return beef mixture to skillet.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except hamburger buns.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Spoon mixture evenly over bun halves.
This makes 2 servings, but may be enlarged.

title: crawfish pies or casserole
directions: Melt margarine. Saute onions, celery and bell peppers. Blend in soup. Remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients and stir. Season to taste. Put in dish. Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: mary's corn chowder
directions: In a medium saucepan, add water, cubed potatoes and chopped onion and cook until tender.
Add creamed corn, evaporated milk and butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until hot.
Do not let liquid boil.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook stuffing per directions on box.
Mix soups together.
Dab a little soup on the bottom of your dish.
Layer chicken then dressing.
Top with remaining soup.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot dog treats
directions: Mix together (to taste) ingredients.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Put in hot dog bun.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: To the boiling water, add strawberry jello, strawberries and syrup, pineapple and pecans.
Mix well.
Put 1/2 mixture in dish. Refrigerate.
When set, spread the sour cream over it.
Pour rest of mixture carefully on top.
Refrigerate.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add whole eggs; beat well.
Add flour.
Add jam and jelly, raisins and soda to mix.
Add milk and nuts.
Makes 3 layers.
Grease pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cookiewiches
directions: Line
large
baking
sheet with waxed paper; set aside. In small
saucepan,
over
low heat, melt chocolate, stirring until smooth.
Using tongs, dip cookies into chocolate; shake off excess.
Place
flat
down
on
prepared
baking
sheet. Sprinkle top
of
cookies
with peanuts.
With metal spatula, spread ice cream
on flat side of each of 8 cookies, dividing evenly.
Top with one of remaining cookies, placing flat side on ice cream. Press lightly.
Wrap each sandwich with plastic wrap.
Freeze until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: brains and eggs
directions: Pick when tender in early spring (do not use after it gets big).
Wash real good and put in large pot filled 1/2 full of water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour off this water and drain real good. Put some more water in poke salad.
Add ham hock (or vegetable oil) and salt.
Let cook on low heat until tender.
May put boiled eggs in to take out some of the bitter taste.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli as directed on package.
Make sauce of soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder (if used).
Layer chicken, sauce, broccoli and cheese (if desired) in a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
End with broccoli on top and top with cheese, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, mix grated potatoes, grated onion and pepper. In nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Put potatoes in skillet.
Cover and cook until bottom is brown.
Turn to brown other side.
Sprinkle parsley on top.
Serves 4.

title: fig jam
directions: Boil figs in water.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Drain and rinse thoroughly in clear, cold water.
Dry figs, getting out as much water as possible.
Pick off stems.
Crush figs and measure. Measure 1/2 amount of figs in sugar (1/2 cup of sugar to 1 cup figs).
Mix sugar and figs and just enough water to start boiling. Add a small amount of lemon juice, orange peel or ginger.
Boil until thick.
Watch carefully so it doesn't burn.
Seal in jars.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour, salt and lard, cutting until well mixed.
Beat egg until light; add water and vinegar and mix with flour mixture. Will make 4 crusts.
Can keep in refrigerator 3 to 4 days.
They also freeze well.

title: hot spiced percolator punch
directions: Put pineapple and cranberry juices with water in bottom part of	a
cup percolator.	Put remaining ingredients in top. Perk for 10 minutes until spices permeate.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch square pan.

title: hot creamed crab
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients together; fold in crab and almonds. Pour in 1-quart casserole and bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Yield: 2 1/2 cups.

title: fred's bread
directions: Mix yeast and sugar in warm water; let stand until foam appears.
In a food processor, mix the dry ingredients.
Slowly add the liquid mixture.
Add the egg.
The mixture will form a ball.
Remove to a floured surface and knead briefly.
Let rise 1 hour.
Form into rolls or loaf.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes for loaf or 20 minutes for rolls.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flavorings. Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Beat until smooth; pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: sausage balls
directions: With cheese at room temperature, crumble and mix with sausage. Add Bisquick mix to cheese and sausage mixture.
Use hand to mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Place in greased 13 x 9 2 pan.
350° - 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: ozey
directions: Heat oil in a skillet.
Add meat, spices and salt.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Add peas and cook for 10 more minutes, stirring often.
Add water.
Bring to a boil and add washed rice.

title: fudge nut brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour and cocoa in small bowl.
Add to creamed mixture; fold in nuts.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix well.
Place in casserole.
Top with 3 slices of bacon. Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: In a large bowl cream together butter, shortening and sugar until light colored and fluffy.
Beat in molasses and eggs, set mixture aside.
In another large bowl, combine flour, salt, baking soda, ginger, cloves and cinnamon. Blend thoroughly with a wire whisk.
Gradually mix flour mixture into creamed ingredients until dough is blended and smooth.
Roll dough into 1 1/2 inch balls. Dip tops in sugar, place 2 1/2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Add garlic and green pepper; saute lightly.
Add bouillon, soy sauce, vinegar, brown sugar and pineapple with juice.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice. Cover and remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.

title: tropical punch
directions: Mix all juices and serve over ice.

title: fantastic delight
directions: Combine pudding mix (dry) with cottage cheese and pineapple. Mix until smooth.
Fold in topping. Serves 8.

title: hidden valley ranch pasta primavera
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Stir in olive oil, salad dressing mix and vegetables.
Heat and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread nuts and coconut on a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Fix mix as directed on box; pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together; spoon over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Brown onion in olive oil and set aside.
Cook shells.
While shells are cooking, brown 1/2 pound butter, being careful not to burn.
When shells are done, drain and mix with the cheese and onion until everything is blended together.
Add 1/2 pound browned butter and mix again.

title: mozzarella spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, salt and pepper and drain.
Add Parmesan cheese, tomato sauce and spaghetti spices.
Simmer for approximately 30 minutes.
Boil and drain spaghetti.
Place spaghetti on a large platter or in a casserole dish and cover with meat sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Place in hot oven until cheese melts.

title: italian chicken
directions: Put chicken in an 8 1/2 x 11-inch casserole dish. Cover with dressing. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: tabouli (middle east)(serves 6)
directions: Some 3 hours before meal time, place uncooked bulgur wheat in bowl and pour boiling water over bulgur.
Cover with towel and let soak for 1 hour.
Drain well.
Stir in other ingredients and chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Serve garnished with halved cherry tomatoes and lemon slices.
Can be used as a grain dish or as a salad and makes an ideal pita bread stuffing.
Leftovers can be added to soup. Just add to crock-pot 1/2 hour before serving.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes (Bundt cake pan or tube pan).

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in bowl.
Cut in shortening until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup mixture for topping.
Mix molasses and baking soda with 2 cups warm water in bowl.
Add to flour mixture and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle reserved mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until cake tests done.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and crisco with pastry blender until crumbly.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage in salted water until very tender; drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Add cheese and allow to melt over low heat. When cheese has melted, add mushroom soup and blend.
Add boiled cabbage and mix well.
Add bread crumbs until of proper consistency, about 3/4 to 1 cup.
Season to taste.
Put in a 2-quart casserole; sprinkle bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° about 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly and hot.

title: chopped herring
directions: Put all ingredients through grinder, using entire jar of herring, including onion and juice.
Taste, if too sour, add sugar; if too sweet, add vinegar.

title: fruit delight
directions: Place fruit in large bowl. Combine vanilla pudding mix, orange drink mix and pineapple juice. Pour over fruit and stir gently. Chill overnight before serving. Good for breakfast.

title: favorite sugar cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients real well.
Chill dough several hours. Roll out to 1/8 to 1/4-inch thickness.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: spicy scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In lightly oiled casserole dish, place layer of potatoes, salt and pepper and lightly sprinkle with flour, then place layer of onions.
Alternate potatoes and onions until all are used.
Heat milk and margarine and Ro-Tel tomatoes and green chilies.
Pour liquid over potatoes; cover with foil and bake 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake additional 30 minutes.

title: jeanne's fresh apple cake
directions: Beat oil, vanilla, eggs, sugar and milk or water by hand. Sift together salt, flour, soda and cinnamon.
Add to first mixture.
Dice and fold in apples.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring the vinegar, water and salt to a boil.
Wash cukes. Place the onion and dill in bottom of jar.
Pack cukes and cover with solution.
Process in hot water bath for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix crab meat, scallops and shrimp.
Add seafood seasoning to taste.
Melt 1/4 pound butter.
Pour over mixed seafood.
Add white wine until it covers seafood.
Put in 350° oven, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Add Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs to top 10 minutes before casserole is finished.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crescent cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion until onion is transparent; drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, mushrooms, parsley, salt, oregano and pepper; set aside.
Unroll 1 package of rolls and separate dough into triangles.
In lightly greased 9-inch pie plate, arrange triangles with pointed ends to the center and press edges together to form a pie shell.
Separate eggs; beat together whites from 3 eggs plus yolks from 2 eggs.
Pour half of beaten egg mixture over pie shell.
Spoon meat mixture into shell; arrange cheese slices on top.
Spread with remaining beaten egg.
Mix reserved egg yolk with water and set aside.
Unroll second package of rolls; place 4 sections of dough together to form a 12 x 6-inch rectangle.
Press edges and perforations together; roll dough into a 12-inch square.
Brush edges of bottom crust with egg yolk/water mixture; place dough on top of filling.
Trim; seal and flute edges.
Cut slits in top crust.
Brush top with the remaining egg yolk/water mixture.
Loosely cover edge with foil strip to prevent over-browning.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cover center of pie loosely with foil and bake 20 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: millet gourmet loaf
directions: Soak soy beans overnight in water to cover.
Cook millet by steaming 1/2 cup hulled millet in 2 cups water and 1/2 teaspoon salt for 30 to 40 minutes.
Grind soy beans and onion medium fine.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Place broccoli in 1-qt. casserole.
Blend soup, milk and salt; stir into broccoli.
Melt butter; toss with saltines.
Sprinkle on broccoli.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: giant chalupa
directions: Layer in order listed.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add to Raisin Bran.
Mix oil, eggs and buttermilk and add to cereal mixture.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Mixture keeps 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: brie and phyllo
directions: Butter a baking sheet.
Use 5 sheets of phyllo and brush with butter.
Set Brie cheese on phyllo, pull up phyllo and tuck edges. Use 5 sheets of phyllo and brush with butter.
Place Brie, tucked sides down.
Pull edges up and tuck.
Fold remaining phyllo into a 1-inch strip and wrap to make a flower; butter.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashioned raisin bars
directions: Combine raisins and water.
Bring to boiling; remove from heat.
Stir in salad oil.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in sugar and egg.
Sift together dry ingredients; beat into raisin mixture. Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 20 minutes, or until done.
Dust with powdered sugar; cut into bars when cool.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, at medium speed, cream margarine and sugars.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until light and fluffy.
Add oil, vanilla and almond extract.
Beat until well mixed.

title: baked apples
directions: Core apples.
Pierce skin.
Place in 2-quart glass dish. Spoon sugar, cinnamon and butter into cavity.
Cover and cook until tender.
(Let stand before testing doneness.) Microwave as follows:
One apple for 2 to 3 minutes; two apples for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes, four apples for 4 to 5 minutes and six apples for 6 to 6 1/2 minutes.

title: cafe remy
directions: Brew a pot of coffee.
Add flavorings.
Pour into cups and add one teaspoon cocoa and one teaspoon sugar per cup.
Garnish with whipped cream on top, along with chocolate and red candy sprinkles and a chocolate-covered strawberry on top.

title: kathy's prune cake
directions: In large bowl, blend sugar and oil; add eggs and mix well. Sift all dry ingredients together and mix into the batter alternately with buttermilk.
Add nuts, prunes and vanilla.

title: scalloped asparagus
directions: Drain asparagus and save juice.
Put into baking dish.
Put chopped eggs on top of asparagus.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Thicken asparagus juice by adding cheese and 1 tablespoon of butter.
Pour over asparagus and top with choice of toppings. Serves 6.

title: spiced cranberry orange relish
directions: Cook cranberries with sugar and orange juice.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.	Simmer, covered, until skins burst 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in orange rind, ginger, nutmeg and cloves.
Cool; cover to refrigerate.
This will make about 3 1/2 cups.

title: chinese noodle candy
directions: Melt chips in double boiler, stirring constantly.
When completely melted, add noodles and peanuts.
Stir well as thoroughly as possible.
They will be stiff.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let harden completely.
Remove from paper and store in covered container in a cool place.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Cut chicken into
1-inch
pieces; set aside.
Blend soy sauce into cornstarch;
stir
in
sherry,
sugar,
ginger
and salt. Preheat wok or
large skillet over high heat.
Add oil. Stir-fry green peppers and
onions
in
hot oil for 2 minutes; remove.
Add walnuts to wok;
stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes or until golden brown. Remove.
Add
more
oil
if needed for chicken. Add
the chicken
pieces
and
stir-fry
for
2 minutes; remove.
Repeat for remaining chicken.
Return chicken to wok. Stir
soy mixture and add to the chicken.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in vegetables and walnuts.
Cover and cook for 1 minute.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter with the brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to the peanut butter mixture.
Mix until blended well.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Heat butter and marshmallows in microwave or on top of stove until melted. Add Rice Krispies.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet. Cut in squares when cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In 3 quarts water, boil chicken, onions, bell pepper and pimentos.
Remove chicken and cube.
Boil noodles in chicken broth. When noodles are tender, add cream of chicken soup, sour cream, cheese and chicken.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 375° until bubbly.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with bread crumbs and 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted and golden brown.

title: red velvet cake
directions: *Substitute for buttermilk 1 cup milk and 1 tablespoon lemon juice or vinegar.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt 8 Milky Way bars and 1 stick oleo; set aside.
Cream the granulated sugar and 1 stick oleo.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time. Add the baking soda, flour and buttermilk.
Add nuts and vanilla. Fold in candy mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dark cherry salad
directions: Soften cream cheese with a small amount of cherry juice to make paste.
Fold in drained fruit and Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: miracle cherry pie
directions: Combine in a saucepan package of vanilla pudding, sugar, salt, lemon juice and water.
Add can of pitted tart red cherries with juice.
Cook and stir to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and a few drops of red food coloring.
Chill in baked 8-inch pie shell.

title: divinity
directions: Stir sugar, corn syrup, water and salt until dissolved.
Boil to spin thread stage (240°).
While syrup is cooking, beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly pour 1/2 of syrup over egg whites, beating constantly.

Cook remaining syrup to crack stage (265°). Slowly pour heavy syrup in candy mixture and continue beating. When mixture holes its shape, add vanilla and nuts and drop from teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add ingredients in order.
Put 3/4 batter in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Top with 1 can cherry pie filling.
Spoon remaining batter on top.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix in pan the sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Put on medium heat and cook until it starts to boil.
Remove from heat. Cool for 1 minute and add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together with hand mixer. Dip for apple slices, grapes, strawberries, bananas, etc.

title: squeaky beans
directions: Fry bacon; save grease from bacon.
Put drained beans, vinegar, sugar and crumbled bacon along with 2 to 3 tablespoons of grease in pan.
Cook with lid for 20 minutes; then remove lid and cook down until juice is syrup and almost gone.
Beans will turn dark.
Syrup should not be cooked all the way out.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Cream
together
the	first 5 ingredients.
Mix the next 6 ingredients together.	Add to the creamed
mixture
and
mix	until
all ingredients are coated. Drop on a greased cookie sheet using a teaspoon.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Cool before serving.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix
all ingredients and pour into greased muffin pans. Bake at 425° until light brown.

title: master baking mix
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and sift 3 times.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender or 2 knives until mix resembles cornmeal. Stir in dry milk. Store in covered container at room temperature.

title: st. paul's rice
directions: Crumble sausage, brown and drain. Boil water, rice and chicken noodle soup for 7 minutes. Add sausage, bell pepper, onion, celery and almonds. Mix well and pour into casserole. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Mix butter and sugars; add vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well. Add chocolate chips.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: bacon and cheese pie
directions: Place onion on bottom of pie shell, then alternate bacon and cheese until used.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Pour slowly over.
Custard like consistency when done.
Test for doneness by inserting knife in center until it comes out clean.

title: california party punch
directions: Mix all juices together, adding amounts of water as directed on cans. Dip out ice cream and sherbert and add to juices. Chill. Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: turkey burgers
directions: In a large bowl, combine the turkey breast with cheese; add onion powder, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Mix well and form into 6 patties. Place burgers in skillet coated with nonstick cooking spray. Cook patties 3 to 4 minutes per side or until juices run clear.

title: sponge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Whip eggs on high for 2 minutes.
Add sugar and whip on high for 8 minutes.
Add flour and baking powder; on low, beat 2 minutes more.
Add juice and extract; beat 2 minutes more.
Put into ungreased tube pan.
Bake until cake springs back when touched, about 30 to 35 minutes.
Turn upside down and cool before removing from pan.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In a large kettle, cook the salt pork until lightly browned. Remove; set aside.
Add the onions to the drippings; cook until tender.
Return the salt pork to the pan.
Add the potatoes, clam liquid plus enough water to yield 4 cups, salt and Tabasco. Simmer until the potatoes are tender, 20 to 25 minutes.
Add the clams, half and half, milk and butter.
Heat, but do not boil. Serve hot.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream butter, sugar and eggs. Add sour cream with soda and dry ingredients. Mix in large amount of vanilla. Pour into greased tube Bundt pan. Sprinkle on topping made of 1/4 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 cup chopped nuts. Dot with extra butter. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: garbanzo dip(excellent)
directions: Blend everything in blender.
Add lemon juice and olive oil little by ???.

title: quiche
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Blend the next 4 ingredients until smooth.
Stir in the meat and other ingredients.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 minutes (knife should come out clean).

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat until smooth.
Add flour and milk alternately until mixed well.
Add salt and vanilla and beat well.
Add baking powder and beat well. Pour into greased and floured Bundt cake pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour, then bake at 350° for 15 more minutes.
Do not open door while cake is cooking.
Cool in pan for about 15 minutes before removing.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Brown sausage in pan.
Pour off grease and add cheese to sausage until melted.
Pour into bowl.
Add Bisquick and stir. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
May be stored in freezer before baking.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake corn bread according to directions on package.
Cool and crumble in large bowl.
Add corn, bacon, tomatoes, bell pepper, onion and mayonnaise.
Mix well.

title: lemon jello mold
directions: Prepare lemon Jell-O and cool for 1/2 hour.
Using mixer, add Cool Whip and lemonade.
Place in deep bowl, not a mold.
This is light and beautiful.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Fry mushrooms in butter and oil; set aside.
With oil and butter left over, add onion and stems of mushrooms and fry.
Mix the bread crumbs, chives and bacon bits to onion and mushroom stems.
Add sour cream; mix altogether.
Fill mushrooms and broil when ready to eat.

title: curried fruit
directions: In medium saucepan melt butter.
Drain all fruit and mix together.
Combine curry, sugar and cornstarch.
Add to fruit mixture.
Stir gently.
Top with extra cherries.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and syrup and vanilla, then pecans.
Pour in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chips and oleo.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Put into a log shape in foil, then roll in coconut and roll up again. Refrigerate.
Slice into 1/4-inch rounds when cold.

title: impossible french apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 10-inch pie plate.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cream together the next 3 ingredients; spread on cooled crust.
Beat the next 2 ingredients about 2 minutes; spread over cheese layer.
Put more Cool Whip and nuts on top.
Chill well.

title: fresh blueberry cobbler
directions: In bottom of baking pan or large baking dish, melt margarine. Add milk; do not stir.
Sift flour and sugar; add to dish.
Do not stir.
Add blueberries.
Bake at 350° until crust rises to top and browns.
May use peaches in place of blueberries.

title: honey chicken
directions: Combine butter, honey, mustard, salt and curry powder in bowl; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Add chicken to prepared dish; coat with honey mixture. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover baking dish and turn chicken.
Bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: berry-filled honeydew melon
directions: Fill melon with berries.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Drizzle apple brandy on top and serve.

title: puppy chow for kids
directions: Spur of the moment or preplanning.

title: broccoli-cheese chowder
directions: Cook broccoli and potatoes in small amount of water until tender.
Add soup, corn and pimento.
Add milk to taste, 3 cups or more.
Add salt to taste.
Add Tabasco sauce to taste in individual servings.
Use about a 3-quart boiler.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown beef and sausage together in a large skillet, stirring until it crumbles. Drain and return to skillet. Add salsa and cubed cheese. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts. Serve warm with chips.

title: navy bean vegetable stew
directions: Cover beans with water.
Bring to boil 2 minutes.
Cover and let stand for 1hour.
Add rest of ingredients and boil until as done as you like them.
Salt and black pepper may be added to suit your taste.

title: blueberry smoothie
directions: Blend until smooth.
Creamy and icy.
Eat with a spoon.

title: homemade chili
directions: Place meat in heavy pot.
Cook slowly until dry.
Add salt, pepper, cumin powder and garlic (chopped fine).
Let brown slightly.
Add paste and chili.
Cover with water and simmer 2 hours.
Add 2 cups Brown Bty beans (any brand) if desired.

title: honey buns
directions: In small bowl, combine nuts, honey and 1/3 cup margarine. Pour into ungreased 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding with Cool Whip. Add all other ingredients and mix well.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Layer in 13 x 9-inch oblong dish:

title: monkey bread - garlic
directions: Thaw bread dough.
Break into 2 to 3-inch pieces.
Melt butter and add garlic.
Dip bread into butter mixture and drop into angel food cake pan or Bundt pan.
Pour leftover butter on top.
Let rise for 2 hours and then bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert onto a serving dish.
Serve hot.
Great for a buffet.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together (do not drain pineapple) and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: paso le  (soup)
directions: Brown ground meat and onions.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook 1 hour.
Add water if needed.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together oil, sugar and eggs. Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Mix with oil mixture. Add apples and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle the batter with chips. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix ingredients and store in jar.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: broccoli casserole with almonds
directions: Cook broccoli until just tender.
Drain and place in buttered casserole.
Make a sauce of the butter, flour, salt, pepper and milk; then add cheese.
Sprinkle top with crumbs and bacon.
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes, or until bubbling and brown on top.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Cook onion until soft.
Add dry ingredients, mixed together.
Then add ketchup, vinegar, water and brown sugar. Bring to a boil.
For spareribs, chicken and steak.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring to boil the crushed pineapple and its juice.
Add the jello; simmer until the jello dissolves.
Cool mixture.
Cream together the cream cheese and the sugar.
Add the baby food apricots to the cream cheese-sugar mixture.
After the jello-pineapple mixture has slightly thickened, add the cream cheese-sugar mixture, then add the Cool Whip.
Pour into glass dish (8 x 13 x 2-inch).
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: oven-baked rice
directions: Measure rice and salt into casserole with tight-fitting cover (or cover dish with aluminum foil) and add boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: good batter
directions: Good for deep frying chicken, fish, onion rings, etc.

title: kahlua chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, eggs, water, sour cream, Kahlua and vegetable oil.
(If chocolate chips are used, stir in after mixing.)
Beat at low speed to blend in mixer.
Increase speed and beat for 3 to 5 minutes.
(Stir in chips if used.)
Pour into a 10-inch Bundt or tube pan that has been greased and floured or sprayed with Baker's Joy.
Bake at 350° for 36 to 46 minutes, until cake tester comes out clean. Cool in pan on rack for 30 minutes.
Loosen from pan and remove pan.
Cool completely on rack.

title: sister harper's smothered fried potatoes
directions: Put oil in large iron skillet and heat.
Add potatoes and chopped onion.
Slow-fry until tender (soft).

title: sausage and egg casserole(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Place
cubed
bread
in
greased 8 x 12-inch casserole. Top with
cheese.
Brown
sausage
and	drain.	Place drained sausage on top of cheese.
Beat eggs with 2 1/2 cups milk and mustard. Pour
over	bread,	cheese and sausage.
Refrigerate overnight. Next day dilute soup with 1 1/2 cups milk and pour over
other ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
This makes a great brunch dish.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line jelly roll pan with aluminum foil or waxed paper; grease.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; set aside.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Grill pork chops over a low heat coal bed while basting with the sauce.
Marinate the chops for 12 to 36 hours before grilling.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix water, sugar and flour together in saucepan on low heat until thickened.
Remove from heat; add Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool in refrigerator.
Add strawberries.
Pour in baked pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients and refrigerate.
Pour over chocolate cake.
You may pour over cake while still warm instead of refrigerating if a richer taste is desired.

title: persion chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into buttered casserole. Cover with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked apples
directions: Arrange apples in baking dish, sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pour soda over apples and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm, cold or partially frozen.

title: pecan pork chops
directions: Heat oil in skillet. Add pork chops coated with the bread crumbs. Top each side with maple syrup, then sprinkle on pecans. Cook until done.

title: fruity daiquiri punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine orange juice concentrate, lemonade concentrate and daiquiri mix.
Stir in water and peach nectar. Chill until needed.
At serving time, add carbonated beverage, ice cubes or ice ring and float strawberries atop punch.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 15 cups or 20 (6 ounce) servings.

title: good sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, then vanilla.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to first mixture and stir with spoon.
Roll in balls not quite the size of a walnut.
Dip one side in sugar.
Put on cookie sheet, sugar side up, and flatten with a glass.
Bake at 350°.

title: luscious lemon bars
directions: Mix flour and 1/3 cup confectioners sugar in a medium size bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles small peas.
Mixture will be dry and crumbly.
Press in bottom of ungreased 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes, or until lightly golden.

title: moyette's
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion, bell pepper and garlic until done.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients, smashing olives with fingers.
Cook on low heat 10 to 20 minutes.
You can add small amount of olive juice to the mixture, if you desire.
"Pick" out a pocket in each roll saving crumbs.
The pocket should be 1/2-inch from bottom and all around edges, making an "envelope".
Fill the hollowed out bun with the olive mixture to top.
Seal with crumbs saved.
Very gently, roll in egg and then in cracker crumbs, repeat again.
Deep fry until golden brown (can pan-fry).
Drain well on paper towels.
A Florida favorite!

title: baked eggs
directions: Combine all ingredients except the eggs and milk in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Whisk together the eggs and milk and pour over the top.
Refrigerate overnight.
In morning, bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt margarine in pan. Put in a 9 x 13 pan and sprinkle crushed graham crackers on top of margarine. Sprinkle coconut, chocolate chips and walnuts on top of graham crackers. Pour Borden milk over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Put chicken breasts down in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with one layer of Swiss cheese.
Thin soup with 1/2 can water; heat and pour over chicken and cheese.
Mix stuffing with melted butter or margarine; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fettuccine straw and hay
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter.
Cook vegetables, meat and herbs in butter over medium-high heat until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring often.
Do not overcook.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
In a heavy saucepan, bring milk almost to a boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce to medium-low heat.
Add cream cheese.
Whisk constantly for 7 to 8 minutes or until melted and smooth.
Stir in 1 cup of Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Arrange hot, cooked pasta in a large serving bowl or platter.
Pour vegetable mixture over pasta; toss to mix well.
Pour cream sauce over pasta; toss to mix well.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add flour, salt and egg yolks. Beat egg whites until peaks form. Fold egg whites into mixture. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350°.

title: punch
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar and 2 cups water; simmer.
Cool.
Chill. Make ahead of time, then in a big pot, mix pineapple, orange and lemon juice and 7-Up and the chilled sugar water.
When ready to serve, put in two trays of ice cubes.
Very good!!

title: casserole potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Melt oleo; stir into crumbs and set aside. Use 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Mix the first 5 ingredients in order given and half of the buttered crumbs; stir together. Sprinkle the remainder of buttered crumbs on top.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: crustless brownie pie
directions: Combine ingredients (except nuts).
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in buttered pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: 3 day slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine cabbage, onions and bell pepper.
Set aside.
In saucepan, mix sugar, vinegar, oil, salt, celery seed and mustard seed.
Mix well and bring to a boil. Set aside to cool.
Pour over cabbage, onions, etc.
Mix together and refrigerate.
Will keep for 4 weeks.

title: irish creme
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. It has always been a tradition to share this treat with friends and family during the holidays.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Heat applesauce until hot.
Put in jello.
Stir real good; let cool.
Add 7-Up and pecans; mix good and chill.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Bring water, carrots, celery, and onions to a boil.
Mix melted butter and flour until smooth.
Stir into boiling mixture, then add pepper and cheese.
Stir until cheese has melted.
Then add the broccoli.
After boiling for 2 minutes, add the milk and half-and-half.

title: asparagus chicken bake
directions: Melt butter in 8-inch square pan or small, shallow casserole. Drain asparagus and reserve liquid (1/2 cup).
Arrange asparagus in melted butter.
Add chicken and sprinkle with cheese.
Prepare muffin mix according to package directions.
Carefully spoon batter on top of cheese as evenly as possible.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel
potatoes; cut in 1/8 inch slices.
Combine mayonnaise, sour
cream,
horseradish,	celery	seed and salt; set aside.
In another
bowl
mix	parsley
and
onion.
In large serving	bowl arrange layer of potatoes; salt lightly.
Cover with layer	of mayonnaise,
sour cream mixture, then layer of onion
mixture. Continue layering, ending with layer of onion and parsley.	Do not
stir.	Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours before serving. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: water chestnut appetizers
directions: Drain water chestnuts; marinate in soy sauce for at least 4 hours.
Cut bacon slices in thirds and wrap around chestnuts and secure with toothpick.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes. Pour sauce (mix catsup and sugar together) over chestnuts; bake for about 30 minutes or until sauce turns brown.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Prepare jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Add lemon juice.
Add frozen strawberries and dissolve; cool.
Add pineapple (juice also) and the mashed banana.
Take half and put in mold.
Chill until set.
When set, spread sour cream on top.
Add rest of mixture, which has cooled.
Let jello set in refrigerator for 4 hours or overnight.

title: quick minestrone soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in oil; add garlic powder.
Add remaining ingredients.
Soft boil for 30 minutes.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt and baking powder together and set aside. Cream shortening and sugars, add eggs and vanilla. Mix well. Add flour mixture and mix well. Add corn flakes and coconut. Mix well. Grease cookie sheets and drop by teaspoonfuls. Bake at 350 degrees for 7 minutes.

title: tomatensalat(tomato salad)
directions: Mix together salt, dried thyme vegetable oil, worcestershire sauce, dried basil, vinegar & onions.
Toss with tomatoes.
Chill for about an hour and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: sweet bread dough
directions: Combine sugar, salt, yeast and 2 cups flour.
In a 2-quart saucepan (low heat), heat milk and butter to 125°.
Using mixer on low, beat liquid into dry ingredients.
Increase speed to medium and beat 2 more minutes.
Scrape bowl often.
Beat in eggs and 2 cups flour.
Beat 2 more minutes.
With spoon, add enough flour to make a soft dough (4 1/2 cups).

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes and combine with rest of ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish.

title: sunny-side grapefruit
directions: Rinse grapefruit halves; sprinkle with brown sugar.
Place on 10 X 15 - inch baking sheet.
Broil for 3 to 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield: 2 Servings.

title: cream dream pie(frozen)
directions: Soften ice cream and mix well with Cool Whip.
Then spread into pie crust.
Decorate however you want with Saran Wrap or plastic insert from bought pie crust.
Freeze for 2 hours.
Serve.

title: crispy baked fish
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Stir dry mustard into finely crushed cracker crumbs.
Beat egg white and milk in bowl.
Spread crumbs in shallow bowl.
Dip fish fillets into egg/milk mix, then coat fillets on all surfaces with cracker crumbs.
Bake on baking sheet for 15 minutes or until coating is crisp.
Serve with lemon wedges or yogurt sauce.

title: quick broccoli and cheese
directions: Boil broccoli until half done.
Pour into colander and drain for 10 minutes.
Return broccoli to pot.
Add margarine, salt, pepper and cheese.
Heat over very low fire until all cheese is melted.
Serve immediately or can be reheated to serve later.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Mix eggs, sugar and pumpkin together; add to flour mixture; stir, mixing well. Grease a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet and line with waxed paper; grease paper also and pour in batter.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Before done, take a kitchen towel, sprinkle with powdered sugar and rub in.
When done, turn onto towel and roll up with paper on.
Let cool 30 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine beef, sausage, rice, salt, pepper and egg.
Form into 6 oval patties.
Place in an 11 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: the best toll house cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together the first 3 ingredients. Add the well beaten eggs.
Stir in the salt, baking soda, baking powder, vanilla and flour.
Next, using a blender, grind to a fine powder the oatmeal. Add the Hershey bar, which has been frozen. Blend this to a fine powder.
Add the blender contents to the first mixture.
Add the chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix everything together.
Place golf ball size cookies on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake about 10 to 13 minutes, no more.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Chop onion small, place in frying pan (or large skillet) and add a little vegetable oil and brown.
Add ground beef and brown. Discard juices.
Put soup and sour cream in pan with ground beef and stir.
Let simmer about 5 minutes to warm and then use flour to thicken.
This Stroganoff should be thick almost like sauce.
Let simmer about another 5 minutes.
Serve over noodles with a side salad.

title: chicken livers in sour cream
directions: Cut chicken livers in half and gently saute them in the butter in a large skillet, turning frequently, for about 5 minutes. Remove livers; saute green pepper in same pan for 5 minutes. Sprinkle flour over green peppers and stir well.
Add sour cream and chicken broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
Add mushrooms, parsley, onion, salt and pepper to taste and Accent.
Just before serving, add livers to the sauce and heat gently, but thoroughly.

title: rum cake
directions: Sprinkle nuts in bottom of greased and floured Bundt pan. Combine pudding, cake mix, eggs, water, oil and rum.
Blend.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into pan.

title: snack mix
directions: Pour over 2- 12 oz. packages our family oyster crackers.
Mix well and let set for at least one hour.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Prepare grits according to box directions.
Add small amount of grits to beaten eggs.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook over low flame until cheese melts.
Pour into prepared casserole.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes; let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoons in hot grease.
Cook until barely brown and crisp.

title: spanish rice
directions: Melt shortening in skillet.
Add rice; lightly brown over low heat.
Add onion and green pepper; stir.
Add tomatoes, water, salt and chili powder; bring to a boil.
Turn heat down to medium or lower; cover and let simmer for about 15 minutes.
Uncover and remove from heat.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dressing for your pig roast
directions: Cook celery, onions and sage.
Break bread and add cooked veggies and eggs, then milk.
Add the sauerkraut.
We put dressing in a clean pillow case, then stuff into pig.

title: almost heaven cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan or baking dish.
When done, take from oven and prick with fork while still hot.
Pour pineapple over top.
Blend pudding with milk and beat in softened cream cheese; spread over layer of pineapple.
Then cover with whipped topping.
If desired, cake may be garnished with chopped nuts and coconut.

title: delicious pie
directions: Blend butter and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients to butter and sugar; pour in crust and freeze until ready to serve.

title: mud toast
directions: Mix cinnamon, sugar and butter into a paste.
The measurements are approximate, depending on how many slices of bread or particular taste.
Spread mixture on bread.
Place under broiler until desired texture is achieved.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine, vanilla and confectioners sugar into balls.
Chill overnight.
Melt paraffin and chocolate bits in double boiler and put balls in with toothpick.
Keep on low heat.

title: my great-grandmother's "raisin sauce for ham"
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar, salt and cornstarch together.
Add water and ground cloves.
Add raisins, vinegar and butter.
Heat, stirring often.
Mixture will thicken in a few minutes.
Serve hot along with your ham dinner.
It's so easy and so delicious!

title: caramel brownies
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Take 1/2 of the mixture and press in the bottom of the pan.
Bake at 350°
for 6 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter over low heat in large saucepan.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly.
Stir in broth and cream; heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add sherry.
Stir in chicken and spaghetti (mushrooms may be added).
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: crab and shrimp casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and turn into 1-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with 1 cup bread crumbs and 1 tablespoon melted butter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: 3 layer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add milk and flour.
Alternately add eggs
one
at a time; mix well; add vanilla last.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 3 (9-inch) cake layers.
Grease and flour pans.

title: aunt pat's baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
To speed up this recipe, you can bring beans to a boil and soak for 2 hours.
Drain beans and place in ovenproof pot with tight-fitting lid.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Add molasses, onion, tomatoes, hot sauce and pork with fat.
Cover and bake in a 250° oven for 12 hours.
If dry, add tomato juice.

title: breaded asparagus
directions: Dip cooked asparagus spears in beaten egg.
Then roll in fine dry bread crumbs or cracker meal and saute in butter or margarine until well browned.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in frying pan.
Drain; add Spanish rice and little water.
Cook until bubbly.
Top with cheese.

title: my mom's biscotti
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add cooled margarine, anise and vanilla extracts. In separate bowl, mix together flour, baking powder, salt, almonds and cherries.
Add to creamed mixture. Shape into 2 logs and place on cookie sheet.
Bake 25 mins. at 375°. Remove from oven and slice into one inch slices and toast on both sides. Yields about 4 dozen.

title: seven flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine, sugar and flavorings.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sour cream.
Add flour and baking powder.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours (maybe less).
Check after 1 hour and 10 minutes for doneness.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer lettuce, celery, onions, carrots and frozen peas.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Place in shallow dish and cover with cocktail sauce.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: chunk ham sandwiches
directions: Mash eggs.
Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serve on toasted bread.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: In skillet, in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook half of the chicken until browned; stir often.
Remove.
Repeat with remaining chicken.
In an additional 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook mushrooms and celery until tender and liquid is evaporated; stir often.
Add soup and sour cream; heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet; heat through.
Stir often.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: old timey fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, grated chocolate, cream of tartar or corn syrup and boil slowly.
Stir until ingredients are well blended. Boil to soft ball stage (238°).
Remove from heat.
Add butter (do not stir).
When lukewarm, add vanilla and beat until it creams (shiny appearance disappears).
Fudge will hold its shape when dropped from the spoon.
Spread in buttered pan.

title: he-man's salad
directions: Slice in layers:
lettuce, carrots and celery.
Over each layer sprinkle canned peas and several dabs mayonnaise.
Over whole sprinkle sugar.
Let set for a while (15 minutes) in order to let sugar soak into mayonnaise.
Cut up several slices of bacon into small pieces and fry crisp.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar, yolks of eggs, juice of lemon and grated rind of lemon.
Add to water which flour has been stirred into. Beat the 2 egg whites and fold into the lemon mixture.
Then pour into a prepared pie shell and bake at 400° until knife comes out clean.
The egg whites will form a meringue on top.

title: trade winds salad
directions: Cook elbow macaroni as directed on package.
Rinse and drain. In a large skillet, melt margarine with brown sugar.
Add luncheon meat.
Cook and stir until golden brown.
In a large bowl, combine cooked macaroni, luncheon meat, pineapple, cheese and green pepper. Stir together mayonnaise, sour cream, reserved pineapple liquid and salt.
Add to macaroni mixture; mix well.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve on lettuce.
Garnish as desired.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together; let set for several hours or overnight.

title: cherry pie delight
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar together.
Mix Dream Whip according to package directions.
Add to cream mixture.
Spread half of this over cooled crust.
Spread cherry pie mix over this and top with remainder of cream cheese mixture.
Chill overnight. Sprinkle with pecans.

title: egg rolls
directions: In a large pot, cook ground beef and turkey in butter; cook until meat is done, then add eggs and stir.
Add garlic powder, black pepper and salt.
Soak noodles in water, then add noodles. Stir.
Add onions, diced.
Stir again.
Add coconut juice and cook 5 minutes.
Taste; may have to add more salt and garlic powder. Cool, then roll.
Fry egg rolls in hot cooking oil.
Place on paper towels and enjoy.

title: christmas rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir every 20 minutes during cooking.

title: chicken puff
directions: Combine soup, milk and salt in casserole dish.
Add chicken or turkey and peas or broccoli.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then beat yolks.
Add cheese and carefully fold yolks into the whites.
Pile on top of chicken mixture.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: partridge breast cashew with rice
directions: Heat 1/4-inch oil in skillet.
Cut meat from breasts and cut into bite-size pieces.
Dip pieces in milk, then into flour.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind real good.
Cook until it's real tender and fill jars while hot.

title: chili cornbread fiesta
directions: Brown and crumble beef; drain.
Add chili seasoning mix, salt, tomatoes and corn (tomatoes need to be chopped).
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole.

title: cliff house cobbler
directions: Melt butter or oleo in baking pan.
Make batter of flour, baking powder, sugar and milk.
Pour in pan with butter.
Do not stir.
Place 2 or 3 cups sweetened fruit on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: turtle soup
directions: Brown bones, onions and carrots very slowly in butter in heavy pan.
Add flour and stir until blended.
Add cold beef stock, tomatoes, cloves, salt and pepper.
Heat slowly to boiling; skim, cover, and simmer 2 hours.
Strain stock through a fine sieve and cool quickly.
When cold, remove fat and if necessary clarify soup. Add turtle meat and sherry, bring to a boil and serve with a slice of lemon and chopped egg.
Serves 6.

title: granny and kelli's cherry cobbler
directions: Melt the oleo.
Pour the cherries in the bottom of a Pyrex baking dish; sprinkle the cake mix over the cherries.
Add the nuts by sprinkling over cake mix and pour the melted oleo over the mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, olives and oregano.
Add ground beef if desired.
Simmer covered for 10 minutes.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add beaten egg, sugar and finely cut dates.
Cook in skillet, stirring constantly, at approximately 300° for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and add rice cereal, nuts and vanilla. Form 1-inch balls and roll in coconut.

title: cherry la la
directions: Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese at room temperature with a mixer.
Set aside.
Mix Dream Whip following directions on box. Combine with first mixture.
Pour 2/3 of mixture in pie shell. Cover with pie filling.
Top with remaining mixture.

title: german hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with skins.
Peel and slice thin.
Cook bacon and onion; stir in sugar, mustard, salt and pepper; stir in chicken broth (can be made with cubes).
Stir in vinegar and celery seed. Bring to a boil.
Pour over potato slices, then put in hot oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with hot knockwurst.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Add this mixture to the original starter and let stand, lightly covered, overnight.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all this well.
Cook at about 325° for 1 hour or until middle gets firm.

title: lemon herb butter
directions: Melt butter; add lemon peel and juice, blending well.
Add seasonings to taste.
Keep warm while preparing vegetables.
Serve butter with vegetables.
Makes 1/4 cup or 6 servings.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt together the caramels, butter and milk.
Mix cake according to directions.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan and pour 1/2 batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove cake from oven.
Pour melted margarine over the half-baked cake. Top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour second half of cake batter over top.
Return to oven for another 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt; add beaten egg yolks and pour on gradually the scalded milk.
Cook 15 minutes in a double boiler, stirring until thick.
Cool and add vanilla.
Put in cooked pie shell.
Add 2 or 3 sliced bananas and top with meringue made of egg whites and sugar.

title: steak oscar
directions: Sear steak in butter to seal juices.
Generously season with spices.
Add consomme and gravy.
Cover and cook over low heat approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pork chops bettina
directions: Salt and pepper chops; brown in oil.
Place in shallow oven pan.
Arrange potatoes on top and around sides of chops.
Salt and pepper.
Sprinkle onion on chops, then flour.
Pour milk gently into pan to almost cover chops.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Remove foil and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer to brown.

title: broiled sandwich filling
directions: Broil until done and browned.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding and Cool Whip until pudding is dissolved.
Add pineapple, nuts and marshmallows.
Chill until serving time.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, soup, milk, 1/2 of onion rings, salt and pepper.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onion rings and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: never fail biscuits
directions: Sift together into bowl the flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cut in the 5 Tbsp shortening.
Add buttermilk, gradually blending with fork.
Knead a few times, roll out and cut into desired shape.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Then add beaten eggs. Add flour, baking powder and salt sifted together alternately with the milk.
Add vanilla.
Roll and cut.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° to 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve cold.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Boil noodles for 10 minutes and drain.
Mix noodles, tuna fish and soup together in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese. Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked cracker jack
directions: Melt oleo.
Add brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add soda and cream of tartar.
Stir and pour over popped corn and mix well.
Put in roaster or cookie sheet and bake 1 1/2 hours at 200°.
Stir a couple of times while baking. Store in airtight container.

title: pearl's barbecue(as served at pielemeier's drug store food & fountain)
directions: Serve open face on rye bread with dill pickle wedge.

title: manicotti casserole
directions: Brown ground turkey, if desired.
Stir in tomato sauce, paste, water and brown sugar.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, combine Ricotta, 2 cups Mozzarella, egg and parsley.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, pour 1/3 sauce in bottom of pan.
Layer cooked manicotti noodles, put Ricotta mixture on top.
Pour remaining sauce over top, top with remaining Mozzarella and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: gaufrettes(french waffle cookies)
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Beat in remaining ingredients until batter is smooth.
Drop by tablespoon in each section of hot waffle iron (deep French, Belgian or regular with cover) approximately 3 minutes until light brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: greek marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together. (Double recipe if using marinade for a roast.)
Marinade your favorite meat in mixture overnight in fridge.
Grill meat on barbecue grill.

title: fresh refrigerator bread and butter pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers into 1/8-inch thick slices. Thinly slice green pepper (remove seeds) and onion. Mix all together with salt and celery seed. Let stand for 1 hour. Drain. Combine sugar and vinegar and stir. Pour over vegetables and mix well. Cover and refrigerate. Pickles are ready to eat in about a day. Store, uncovered, in refrigerator. This makes about 5 cups of very good tasting bread and butter pickles.

title: homemade french dressing
directions: Put in jar, shake and store.

title: seven layer mexican dip
directions: Mix refried beans, taco mix and salsa.
Layer in ovenproof casserole dish.
Then in order of ingredients, layer each until complete with cheese.
Heat at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Spread spaghetti in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1 bag crushed potato chips. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Slice and serve.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening. Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour slowly to this mixture. Add 7-Up and vanilla. Bake at 325°. Preheat oven. Bake for 1 hour and 15
minutes or until done.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Mix all together flour, sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon, salt and oil; set aside 1/2 cup mixture and add to it 1 teaspoon cinnamon. To the larger mixture, add buttermilk, soda, egg and vanilla. Pour into 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle on topping. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: liver nipps
directions: Cook stew beef until tender; then cook liver in beef pot for 1/2 hour.
Take meat out of beef broth and let cool.
Grind or grate the meat.
Put your flour, onions, spices, egg and 1 cup of beef in.
Finally, mix all together and drop in boiling broth for 30 minutes or until done.

title: sinful chocolate cake
directions: Stir all ingredients by hand.
Grease (or oil) and flour a Bundt pan.
Pour batter in.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350°.
Cook 15 minutes in pan, then remove to cooling rack.
This is a rich cake, delicious as is or served with ice cream.
It can be frosted or dusted with powdered sugar.

title: pumpkin meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and spices in saucepan.
Gradually stir in pumpkin and milk.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and comes to boiling.
Cook 2 minutes longer and remove from heat. Stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks, return to hot mixture.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour into cooled pastry shell.
Top with meringue.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool pie thoroughly before cutting.

title: chicken and wine in no time
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in bag.
Shake chicken to coat. Brown well on all sides in oiled skillet.
Sprinkle onion soup over.
Pour in white wine.
Add a little water.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: orange-almond cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour round layer pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inch or square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Beat all ingredients, except almonds, 1 tablespoon sugar and the liqueur, in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 3 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle with almonds.

title: miniature cinnamon swirls
directions: Separate roll dough into 2 rectangles.
Spread with margarine; sprinkle with mixture of sugar, cinnamon and raisins.
Roll each rectangle from narrow end to enclose filling; press edges to seal. Cut each roll into 6 slices.

title: spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and melt in oven.
Remove.
In large bowl beat eggs well, then add flour, milk, salt and baking powder and mix well.
Add cheese, spinach and onion; mix well.
Spoon into baking dish and level off.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in medium bowl.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper; mix well.
Set aside.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix in small bowl.
Set aside.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and add sugar.
Cream and add egg yolks (well beaten).
Add nuts.
Add candied fruit.
Add vanilla extract.
Add plain flour with baking powder sifted in.
Add well beaten egg whites.
Mix with hand when too stiff to stir.
Bake in well-greased and floured stem pan for 5 hours at 250° with water in oven above and below.

title: dill bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Combine in mixing bowl cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda, egg and softened yeast.
Add flour to stiff batter, beating well after each addition.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place (85° to 90°) until light and doubled in size, 50 to 60 minutes.
Stir down batter.
Turn into well-greased 8-inch round 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole.
Let rise in warm place until light, 30 to 40 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake.
Brush with butter; sprinkle with salt.

title: different potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes; slice as for scalloped potatoes.
Salt to taste.
Combine sour cream, horseradish, mayonnaise, celery seed and salt.
Set aside.
Combine chopped parsley and onions.

title: yummy cheese spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and Cheddar cheese until blended. Add sherry and curry powder. Mix until soft. Spread on dish. Pour on chutney and spread over top of cheese. Layer on onion tops, then bacon bits. Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: clam dip
directions: Blend soup and cream cheese together with a mixer.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Mix in Worcestershire and lemon pepper to taste. Chill and serve with corn chips.
Serves approximately 20 people.

title: bonnie's nacho dip
directions: Mix beans and taco mix.
Place in bottom of dish.
Layer sour cream, avocado dip and cheese.
Top with olives.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Get the mayonnaise out.
Dice up some onions, about 1 1/2.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Mix bouillon in hot water and set aside.
Saute chicken breasts in 2 tablespoons melted butter until golden brown.
Remove chicken from pan and sprinkle flour into drippings and stir.
Add chicken bouillon to flour and stir until thickened.
Add milk; stir, then add Dijon mustard.
When sauce is bubbling, return chicken to pan and cover for 5 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: eskimo yogurt apples
directions: Wash apples well; polish with clean towel.
Cut off top of each apple; brush with lemon juice to prevent discoloration.
Set aside.
Carefully cut out inside of each apple to leave 1/2-inch shell; brush insides with lemon juice.
Dice removed portions of apples.
Discard core and seeds.
Combine with sugar, raspberries (reserve whole ones for garnish), liquor, coconut and ground almonds.
Fold in yogurt; spoon into apples.
Top each with dollop of whipped cream, a reserved raspberry and sliced almonds.
Cover with apple tops.
Serve immediately!

title: scalloped rhubarb
directions: Add butter to bread and mix well.
Add sugar to rhubarb and mix well.
Combine and place in an oblong greased pan.
Put 1 tablespoon water in each corner of pan.
Sprinkle lightly with red food coloring.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: spinach that kids will eat
directions: Thaw out spinach and squeeze out as much water as possible. Mix with soup and sour cream.
Top with cheese.
(Swiss is good, too.)
Bake at 350° in ungreased casserole dish for about 45 minutes, or until cheese is bubbly and browned.
Serves 4.

title: paella
directions: *Some also use pieces of ham.

title: spiced carrots
directions: Cut carrots in about 1/2 inch rounds.
Cook until tender. Drain and mix with other ingredients and let stand in refrigerator for 8 hours.
Warm before serving.

title: cabbage rolls*
directions: Wash cabbage.
Pull off 8 large leaves.
Simmer leaves in boiling water.
Cover for 5 minutes.
Drain and spread.
Combine ground beef and pork.
Saute in butter until brown.
Add seasoning and rice.
Fill leaves with mixture.
Roll up, folding ends to center.
Secure with toothpick.
Place in greased skillet. Add tomatoes; cover and simmer 45 minutes or bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: heavenly rice
directions: Bring water to a boil; add rice to water and stir.
Let set 5 minutes.
Add pineapple, drained well and marshmallows; stir.
Let set for 1 1/2 hours.
Whip whipping cream.	Fold all together and chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put whole breasts in bottom of casserole with other ingredients on top.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: cherry o cream cheese pie
directions: In medium size bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add condensed milk; stir until well blended.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Put in crust.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Pour a can of chilled cherry pie filling on top of pie.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in an ungreased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or place in an oven cooking bag and place in a large baking pan.
Cook at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into 1/2-inch balls.
Cook at 350° until slightly brown.

title: corn relish
directions: Cook over low heat. Bring to a boil and add 1 pint prepared mustard.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes, stirring constantly. Can in sterile jars.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk all at once, stir only until dough follows fork.
Turn out on lightly floured surfaces, knead 1/2 minute.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Pour butter on.
