Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top.
Roll up jelly roll fashion and cut into 12 pieces.
Place in muffin cups and bake at 425° about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: carrot ring
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased 1 1/2-quart ring pan.
Bake at 375° until set and browned, about 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add mashed bananas, flour, soda (dissolved in buttermilk), nuts, raisins and flavoring.
Bake in greased loaf pan in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cocoa kisses
directions: Beat egg whites in medium bowl until foamy.
Add cream of tartar; beat until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in sugar, a few tablespoons at a time.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in cocoa. Drop batter
by level teaspoons on nonstick cookie sheets which have been sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake in preheated 275° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely before removing from pans. Store in a very dry place.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: that salad
directions: Put all of the ingredients into a large salad or mixing bowl; toss.
Marinate overnight or for several hours in refrigerator. Salad is always better if made the day before serving and allowed to marinate.
Can be used as a main course, with sandwiches or as an accompaniment to roast pork or baked ham.

title: terri's fruit drink
directions: Mix well and chill.
Better than Kool-Aid.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Separate eggs and beat whites until fluffy.
Set aside. Cream butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Beat real good.
Add sour cream. Beat real hard.
Add flavoring and mix in 1 cup flour; beat real hard.
Fold in egg whites.
Again, beat real hard.
Sift together remaining flour, salt and soda.
Add to batter.
Again, beat real hard.
Pour into large greased tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8-inch square baking dish.
In a mixing bowl, beat 4 tablespoons of the butter with the sugar and honey.
Add the nuts, raisins and spices.
Mix well.
Remove the apple cores, but do not cut all the way through the bottoms.
Stuff each apple with nut mixture and place in the baking dish.
Rub the skin of each apple with the remaining 1 tablespoon of butter and sprinkle any remaining nut mixture over top.
Bake until the apples are soft, 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream. Serves six.

title: german-style roast beef salad
directions: Combine beef, pickles, onion and parsley in large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over beef mixture. Blend in.
Chill well before serving.
Serves 4.

title: rigatoni
directions: Brown ground beat; season to taste with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Chop onion; add to meat.
Drain grease off.
Add 1 cup of water.
Add tomato paste.
Stir over medium-high heat until blended.
Add about 1 can of water.
Add sugar, then salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes until thickened.

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: Microwave chocolate, milk and margarine in medium microwavable bowl on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds. Stir until chocolate is completely melted and spread into crust. Refrigerate 30 minutes, until chocolate is firm.
Arrange banana slices over chocolate.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Place in baking dish,
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers or tortilla chips.

title: ooooh-la-la potatoes
directions: Cook
potatoes in skins.
Cool, peel and dice.
Combine cheese and
4 tablespoons butter in large saucepan.
Heat and stir until
cheese in almost melted.
Remove from heat; blend in
sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes and spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with remaining
2 tablespoons butter.
Cover and bake for 25 minutes in a 300° oven.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift the sugar, flour, cinnamon, soda and salt together. Add the oil, beaten eggs, bananas, pineapple, vanilla and nuts. Stir to blend (do not beat). Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: cinnamon orange pancakes(low calorie)
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine all dry ingredients and mix until well blended.
In another bowl, combine all liquid ingredients and orange peel.
Stir well.
Pour liquid ingredients mixture into dry ingredients
and stir only until moistened.
Preheat griddle or skillet for pancakes.
Spray lightly with vegetable oil.

title: cobbler(fat free)
directions: Mix all together and pour on top of fruit.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Saute onions and peppers. Add ground beef and brown until done; drain well. Stir in above ingredients and pour into lightly greased casserole dish. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meal-in-one casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour in buttered casserole dish and top with thick layer of crushed potato chips.
Bake, uncovered, in moderate oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: white sauce lasagna
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in 1 tablespoon oil in large frypan.
Add 1 cup chopped onion and 1 garlic clove.
Saute until tender.

title: special cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake(serves 12 to 16)
directions: Mix and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: marshmallow meringue
directions: Covers 9 or 10-inch pie.
Heat slowly the marshmallows and milk, folding over and over until marshmallows are about half the original size.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla; continue folding until mixture is light and spongy.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Add salt.
Gradually add sugar, beating constantly.
Fold in slightly warm marshmallow mixture.
Pile on pie, joining edges to crust. Place top of pie 3 inches from broiler unit (or flame) for 30 seconds or delicate brown.
Watch it!!
Don't let this good stuff burn.

title: rhett's favorite casserole
directions: Lightly brown ground meat in large skillet.
Add onions and cook until tender,	but not brown.	Place noodles in layer over meat.
Combine sauce
ingredients
and
pour it on top of noodles. Bring to a boil,
cover
and simmer over low heat 20 to 25 minutes until
noodles
are
tender.
Stir in sour cream and mushrooms.	 Heat
just
to
boiling.
Season
to
taste. Serves 6.

title: coconut apricot strips
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, sugar and egg yolks thoroughly.
Measure flour by dipping method.
Stir flour into sugar mixture.
Press and flatten mixture to cover bottom of ungreased oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread with preserves, then with meringue.
Return to oven and bake about 20 minutes until meringue is golden brown. Cool slightly and cut in small bars, about 2 x 1-inch.
Makes about 4 dozen bars.

title: hamburg stroganoff
directions: Mince onions and saute in 3 tablespoons butter (or bacon fat). Add flour; blend well.
Add beef broth and Worcestershire sauce.

title: hazel's buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water or milk until it foams. Stir in enough flour for a soft sponge.
Add egg yolks, salt and Crisco.
Fold in egg whites beaten stiff.
Let rise until double. Shape into rolls of desired shape.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° until roll tests hollow.
Also, great recipe for Pepperoni Rolls.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and cut into slices.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix thoroughly and store in airtight container.
To serve mix 2 or 3 teaspoons in a cup of hot water to taste.

title: dolmas (greek appetizer)
directions: Toast pine nuts in a heavy skillet over medium heat, stirring frequently, for about 5 minutes until golden.
Cool.
Wash rice in cold water and drain.
Heat 3 tablespoons of olive oil in a saute pan over medium-high heat.
Add yellow onion and saute until just soft.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add rice, 1/2 cup of olive oil, green onions, 1/4 cup parsley, mint, pine nuts, cinnamon, allspice, salt and pepper.

title: taco shells
directions: Combine ingredients.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Add more water, if needed (dough will be stiff); let stand 10 minutes.
Shape into 18 balls.
Let stand 10 more minutes.
Roll into very thin 6-inch circles.
Fry on a greased grill or skillet.

title: tamale pie
directions: Bring the water and tomato sauce to boil and add the cornmeal. Cook until thickened. Cook the ground meat with the onions. Add the corn, olives and chili powder. Mix in cornmeal mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Scatter butter evenly over nuts.
Drizzle syrup over nuts. Bake for 1 hour at 250°, stirring every few minutes.
Drain on brown paper bag.
Salt generously and toss to ensure all nuts are covered.

title: pear crisp
directions: Place chopped pears in bottom of dish. Mix other ingredients and spread over pears. Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beau monde veggie dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Allow to sit at least 2 hours before serving.

title: easy milk chocolate fudge
directions: Put chocolate morsels in top of a double boiler.
Place over hot (not boiling) water.
Stir until melted.
Add condensed milk, butter, and vanilla.
Blend until butter is melted.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Spread into lightly oiled square cake pan (8 inch). Cool until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix eggs, milk and bread together.
Set aside.
Mix ground chuck, carrots, onion, cheese, pepper and salt together.
Add bread mixture and mix well.
Put in a loaf pan.
Mix together ketchup, sugar and mustard.
Spread on top of meat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: burger bites
directions: You will need 12 paper hamburger wraps from McDonald's, cut into half.

title: ice cream sandwich dessert
directions: Place 1 scoop of ice cream between 2 chocolate chip cookies. Place sandwich on a dish.
Pour a small amount of chocolate syrup over sandwich.
Add whipped topping and sprinkles.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Diabetic Exchange:
1/2 bread, 1/2 fruit, 1 fat.
You can use graham cracker crust.
Use 1 cup of graham crackers and 2 tablespoons diet margarine.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt oleo in long baking pan or dish. Place chicken in pan or dish; pour rice over chicken. Combine 3 soups and pour over rice. Sprinkle onion soup over the top. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 2 hours. (May vary with chicken size.) Uncover last 30 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: *If using instant potatoes, follow package directions and omit egg and warm milk.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: sausage balls
directions: Form into walnut-size balls and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes (until browned).
I lightly brown my sausage and I also melt my cheese.

title: mandarin chicken
directions: Prepare chicken by removing bones and steaming good size pieces.
Dip in batter and fry in hot, deep fat.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Cover with sauce.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix together in a saucepan sugar, cocoa, milk, and butter. Cook over medium heat, stirring until it comes to a full boil. Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, coconut, peanut butter, and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly, and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper. Cookies will set as they cool.
Yield:
about 30 cookies.

title: 4 way bean dish casserole
directions: Fry bacon crisp; drain green beans.
Place all beans in casserole bowl.
Break bacon and add to beans.
Add catsup and sugar; mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in uncovered baking dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top about 10 minutes before done time.

title: drop teacakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil. Mix together and drop with spoon.
Bake 6 or 8 minutes or until lightly brown on edges.
Remove from cookie sheet and spread on racks.

title: wild rice with minted peas and pearl onions
directions: Cook the rice according to directions and set aside.
Steam the peas over boiling water until tender.
Remove from heat.
Melt the butter in a saucepan and add the peas, onion, mint and sugar. Toss and cook for 2 minutes over medium heat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Gently toss with the wild rice.

title: oven fried chow mein
directions: Combine sesame oil, oyster sauce, shoyu sauce and salt. Place remaining ingredients into foil-lined roasting pan.
Pour sauce over and toss.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: cream cheese brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and 1 egg in a bowl and beat until smooth. Set aside.

title: broccoli-cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch glass or ceramic pie plate.
Heat 1 inch salted water in saucepan to boiling and add vegetables.
Cover and cook until almost tender and drain.
Mix in onion, pepper and cheese.

title: herbal pretzels
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Pour over top of pretzels.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Stir two or three times to coat pretzels.

title: chicken nuggets(makes 25 to 30 nuggets)
directions: You will also need a cutting board, knife, small bowl, measuring spoons, spoon for mixing, dry measuring cups, clean plastic bag, two 9-inch microwave-safe plates, two paper towels, fork or tongs, potholders and a serving plate.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Bring Jell-O and pineapple to boil.
Cool and stir in buttermilk and Cool Whip.

title: honey-bun cake
directions: Prepare 13 x 9 pan (spray or grease and flour) and preheat oven to 325°.
Mix cake mix, eggs, sour cream and oil well with mixture and spread 1/2 mixture in pan.

title: cut-out cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in margarine with electric mixer until particles are fine.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; blend thoroughly.
If needed, dough may be chilled for easier handling.
Roll out dough on floured wax paper.
Roll to 1/8 inch.
Cut into desired shapes. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes, or until lightly browned around the edges.
Decorate as desired.

title: big monster cookies
directions: This recipe makes 80 (5-inch) cookies so you need a very large bowl or dishpan for mixing.

title: round steak with rich gravy
directions: Cut meat into serving sizes.
Sprinkle one side with 1/2 of the flour; pound in.
Turn over and pound in remaining flour. Heat oil in large skillet; brown meat on both sides.
Sprinkle onion soup over meat.
Mix water and mushroom soup and pour over meat.
Cover tightly and simmer 1 1/2 hours until done.

title: honey salad dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Pour oil in slowly, stirring constantly. Chill.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Cook and stir bell pepper, onion and garlic in 1/4 cup dressing in skillet over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Stir in chicken, juice, cumin, pepper and remaining 1/4 cup dressing. Cook for 7 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.
Serve with tortillas.
Serves 6.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain vegetables and pour them in a large bowl.
Bring sugar, oil and vinegar to a boil.
Pour over vegetable mix.
Add salt and pepper.
Refrigerate at least overnight.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil
chicken with
pepper,
salt,
garlic
and
onion. Debone.
Add can milk
mixed
with cornstarch to thicken broth from chicken.
Add can
of
Veg-All (drained) and cooked potatoes; mix all together.
Bake
biscuits and put them on top of chicken ingredients with gravy.
Put
this
mixture
in
oval casserole dish and in oven at 350° to warm through, only about 20 minutes.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl until foamy.
Add sugar, oil, vanilla and zucchini.
Blend lightly.
Sift dry ingredients and add along with nuts and coconut.
Blend well.
Pour mixture into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Combine dressing mix with cream cheese. Spread on bread slices and top with cucumber slices. Sprinkle top with paprika.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add sauce and oregano.

In a 9 x 13-inch pan place biscuits evenly and press together with greased fingers to form a bottom crust. Pour hamburger mixture on top of biscuits. Place Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and somewhat brown on top.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, pumpkin and sugar.
Beat until light. Add dry ingredients.
Beat.
Add nuts.
May add 1/2 cup raisins, if desired.
Use well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crazy casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions in skillet.
Turn heat low and add 1/3 of soy sauce.
Add cabbage and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms, bean sprouts and 1/3 of soy sauce.
Add cooked spaghetti.
Cover; simmer a few minutes.
Serves 6.

title: anthony's oven pancake
directions: Cut sausage links into 1/2-inch slices.
Cook until brown. Drain on paper towels.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Measure flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a separate bowl, beat egg and stir in milk.
Melt butter and add to egg mixture.
Pour egg mixture into flour mixture.
Grease an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Pour batter into greased pan; sprinkle with sausage.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
To serve, cut into squares and serve with Mom's Maple Syrup.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and butter together by hand in a small bowl until combined. Add extract and eggs and stir only until eggs are thoroughly mixed in. DO NOT overmix. Bake in 350° oven until just set. (DO NOT overbake.)

title: campfire bean soup
directions: Arrange a grid over your open fire and position a soup pot over it.
Saute onion and celery in bacon fat until soft.
Cover with water and add potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are soft.
Add ham hock and diced ham.
When the ham hock is warmed through, add navy beans and more water if necessary.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Ladle into bowls and eat around the campfire.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine and cook to desired thickness.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together with thyme, bay leaf, salt, pepper and Italian seasoning.
Add mushroom soup and tomatoes. Stir and heat.
Add instant rice, lower heat and simmer for 5 minutes or until rice is done.
Stir, put in casserole bowl.
Add cheese strips or slice to top.
Place under broiler until cheese melts.
You're ready to serve.
Feeds family of 4 to 6.

title: crystals
directions: Don't make dough too stiff.
Knead until it comes off your fingers.
Separate into three balls.
Let sit at least 20 minutes so dough can relax.
Roll dough thin.
Cut into 4-inch squares. Make two or three slits in each square.
Fry in deep hot oil.

title: high school fudge
directions: Blend all well.
Press in an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: vegetable mold
directions: Let first 3 ingredients set until syrupy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat all together and place in mold.
Chill until firm.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix ingredients; pour butter in mix. Pour in pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana casserole
directions: Heavily butter a shallow casserole.
Cover butter with bananas, sliced lengthwise.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and plenty of butter,
a layer of raisins and pecans.
Repeat layers.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in preheated oven at 325°.
Just before serving, throw a little brandy on top.
Good with pork, poultry and great over ice cream.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion for 5 minutes and drain well.
Add soup, sour cream and carrot.
Melt oleo and stir into dressing. Add Stove Top mix to the other ingredients.
Save some to put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; cool slightly and set aside.
Beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually add gelatin. Beat well.
Stir in pineapple and baby food; fold in whipped topping.
Pour in 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish; cover and chill until firm.

title: herbed chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cool.
Reserve 2 cups chicken broth.
Remove chicken from bones and tear into bite-size pieces.
Place in shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Combine soups and 1 cup broth.
Pour over chicken.
Mix butter and remaining cup of broth and stir into stuffing.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake in 400° preheated oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese(italian style)
directions: Cook macaroni until chewy.
Drain and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese mixture and place under broiler for a few minutes or until cheese is melted and crispy.

title: lemon layer
directions: Mix together flour and oleo; work as pie crust.
Add nuts. Press into 8 x 10-inch pan; bake at 375° for 15 minutes and chill.

title: diabetic banana muffins
directions: Grease and flour or line with paper baking cups 12 muffin cups. Sift flour with baking powder, salt, soda and nutmeg into mixing bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix with dry ingredients only until dry particles are moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Yields 12 muffins.
Each equals 1 1/2 bread plus 1 fat exchange.

title: zucchini l' italienne
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add zucchini, onion and all spices.
Cover; simmer over low heat until zucchini and onion are soft.
Add Swiss cheese; re-cover until cheese is thoroughly melted.
Serves 4.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: In 5 quart Dutch
oven
heat
corn oil over medium-high heat. Add chicken, a few pieces at a time.
Brown well on all sides. Remove chicken.
Drain
excess
fat.
Add
onions
and mushrooms. Cook, stirring, 5 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Stir
in
dumplings.
Add chicken.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat;
cover
and simmer, stirring occasionally, 20 to 30 minutes
or
until
chicken and dumplings are tender. With slotted spoon,
remove chicken and dumplings.
Keep warm. Stir together cornstarch
and
milk.
Stir
into
Dutch
oven. Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute. Serve over chicken and dumplings.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine sugar, syrup and margarine in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Boil gently, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Let cool.
Place pecans in pie shell.
Mix eggs, vanilla and salt in bowl.
Stir in cooled syrup.
Pour over pecans in shell.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: veal stew
directions: In cast-iron pan, brown veal in 1 tablespoon olive oil.
In stock pot, saute garlic, shallots and leeks in the other tablespoon olive oil for 5 minutes.
Add veal when browned.
Add all other ingredients, cover and simmer on low heat for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaves and the bunch of herbs. Taste for salt and pepper.

title: snow ball cake
directions: Cook over medium heat sugar, butter, egg yolks, vanilla and cornstarch	until
thick;
set off and cool.
Slice angel food cake
and
layer angel food cake; on top of this put Cool Whip, pineapple and top this with nuts.

title: gumbo (seafood)
directions: Add soup and grated cheeses to vegetable mix.
Add seasonings and Tabasco.
Add 1/2 can Parmesan cheese.
Take chicken from bone and chop into bite-size pieces.
Add to soup and vegetable mixture.

title: honeyed chicken
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry with paper towels.
Arrange chicken pieces in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan, making sure pieces do not touch.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: amish butterscotch bars
directions: Over low heat, melt sugar, peanut butter and corn syrup. Crush Rice Krispies and add to peanut butter mixture.
Mix well. Spread in an 11 x 16 pan.
Melt chips and spread onto bars.
Chill and cut.

title: black storm
directions: Fill shaker halfway with ice cubes.
Add all ingredients and shake well.
Pour into drinking glass.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Brown chops in hot oil.
Add onion, bell pepper and tomatoes. Sprinkle on rice.
Cook over low heat until rice and chops are done, about 1 hour.

title: coconut-sour cream layer cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, making two 8-inch layers.
When cool, split both layers (take a string and pull through cake layers slowly).
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut, blending well.
Reserve 1 cup sour cream mixture for frosting.
Spread remainder between layers of cake.
Combine reserved sour cream mixture with Cool Whip; blend until smooth. Spread on top and sides of cake.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Spray pan with cooking spray and brown chicken for 2 minutes on each side; remove from skillet. Re-spray pan and cook mushrooms and onions until soft. Add apricot halves, chicken broth, nutmeg and chicken breasts and simmer 6-8 minutes. Mix cornstarch and brandy and add to mixture. Serve over noodles.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice

potatoes. Place in a heavy skillet. Add butter, water and sugar and bring to a boil. Turn heat down and slowly cook for approximately 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender with a medium to thin syrup. Cover with lid while cooking.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, but mayonnaise, in a large bowl.
Blend well.
Add mayonnaise just before serving.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine raw squash, onion, sugar, flour, salt and pepper. Beat eggs and add to squash mixture.
Add melted margarine and mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto hot oiled griddle or skillet. Cook until delicately browned on both sides.
Serve immediately.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Combine cranberries, 1/2 cup sugar and nuts; place in pastry lined pie pan.
Beat eggs; add remaining 1 cup sugar, flour, margarine and shortening.
Pour over cranberry mixture and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: honey and spice crunch
directions: Pour popcorn into a bowl coated with cooking spray; set aside. Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat; stir in next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil, without stirring, 7 minutes or until a candy thermometer reaches 250°.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cinnamon, soda and vanilla; pour over popcorn, stirring to coat.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan. Bake at 250° for 25 minutes or until golden, stirring every 5 minutes.
Stir in dried fruit; cool.
Store in airtight containers.
Yield:
3 quarts.

title: home ec.  refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat eggs. Add eggs and vanilla to sugar mixture.
Sift flour, salt and soda onto wax paper.
Add sifted dry ingredients gradually to the egg mixture and mix thoroughly.
Add pecans if desired.
Press dough together and shape into long rolls about 2 inches in diameter. Wrap in wax paper.
Chill overnight until firm.
Cut dough into thin, uniform slices about 1/8-inch thick.
Place about 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove cookies from baking sheet with spatula.
Cool on cake rack.

title: shrimp vera cruzano
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and garlic in olive oil just until tender.
Add mushrooms, tomatoes and olives.
Cook slowly over low heat.
While vegetables are still crisp, add shrimp and cilantro. Season to taste.
Continue cooking just until shrimp are pink. Serve over rice.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients, then add the others.
Mix well.
Pour into well greased loaf pans, about 1/2 full.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove immediately from pans.
Cool on wire racks.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, eggs, milk, corn, soda, salt and drippings together; set aside.
Saute hamburger and put on paper towel to drain excess grease.
Prepare onion, cheese and peppers.
Place in molds ready to use.
Grease a large skillet and heat.
Sprinkle a thin layer of corn meal in skillet.
Brown slightly and pour 1/2 batter into skillet.
Sprinkle cheese on batter, then spread hamburger over this.
Add onion and peppers.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: magnolia grill cream of vidalia onion soup(serves 8)
directions: Bake bacon until crisp; remove to paper toweling.
Add butter, onions and garlic to bacon.
Cover; cook over low heat, stirring often, until onions are translucent and lightly caramelized.
Add wine, stock, bay leaf and thyme.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and puree soup in food processor or blender.
Pass soup through fine blade of food mill (optional). Chill.
Whisk in cream or creme fraiche or sour cream.
Season with salt, pepper, hot pepper sauce and nutmeg.
Serve in chilled bowls. Garnish with bacon, croutons and chives.

title: cabbage salad(marinated to freeze)
directions: Chop cabbage; sprinkle with salt.
Mix and let stand for 1 hour.
Combine water, vinegar, mustard seed, sugar and celery seed and boil 1 minute.
Cool.
(May be done the day before.)
Chop celery, carrot, onion and pepper and add to cabbage.
Stir cool liquid into all.
Pack into containers if you wish to freeze.

title: herb-stuffed potatoes(nutritious)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake potatoes about 45 minutes.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out inside and mash.
Add remaining ingredients except paprika.
Mix thoroughly.
Spoon potato into shells on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Return to oven for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serves 8. Each serving amount:
1/2 potato equals 1 bread and 1/2 fat.
Cholesterol trace, carbohydrate 21 g, fat 2 g, calories 112, protein 3 g, fiber 2 g and sodium 62 mg.

title: almond pine cone
directions: Spread almonds in a single layer in shallow pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes, stirring often, until almonds just begin to change color.

title: mom's in-a-hurry curry
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Stir in almonds, parsley and butter.
To serve, ladle sauce over rice.

title: pralines
directions: In 2-quart pan (using a wooden spoon), mix sugar, milk, butter, Karo and salt.
Cook to soft ball (about 10 minutes). Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until thickens, about 1 minute.
Drop by a tablespoon on buttered waxed paper. Yields 2 dozen.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Cut potatoes into pieces and place in boiling water.
Cook until tender, approximately 10 minutes. Drain and cool.
Rub 2-quart bowl with garlic.
Discard garlic.
Place potatoes in bowl.
Dissolve bouillon in water.
Add wine. Pour over potatoes. Cover and refrigerate, stirring once or twice.
Drain.

title: buckwheat cakes
directions: Mix yeast and 2 cups warm water.
Add enough flour to make extra thick batter.
Set in warm place to rise overnight.
In the morning, add baking soda, sugar, salt and 1/2 cup warm water.
Mix thoroughly.
If batter is too thick, thin with water to desired thickness for baking.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Then add dry ingredients and stir.
Add oatmeal last.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onion, water and salt in large pot. Simmer, covered, about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Mash mixture a few times with potato masher, but leave some pieces whole.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly, until soup is thoroughly heated.

title: aunt stella's cornbread(origin: unknown)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix soda with milk.
Mix flour, cornmeal and salt.
Add flour and milk alternately to butter mixture.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 30 minutes.
For muffins, bake 17 to 18 minutes. Makes 30 muffins or 1 pan.

title: fluffy no fail frosting
directions: Mix in top of double boiler, beating constantly with mixer, over boiling water 7 minutes.
Add vanilla when thick and fluffy.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix and top with buttered bread crumbs or cracker crumbs. Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corn chowder
directions: In kettle, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pot and reserve.
Pour off all but 3 tablespoons fat.
Add onion and saute until tender (5 minutes).
Blend in flour.
Add water and potato. Bring to a boil and simmer about 15 minutes.
Add corn and milk; heat well.
Crumble bacon and add to chowder.
Season to taste.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown hamburger; then put everything in a crock-pot on low for 3 hours.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In a
5-quart pot, bring tomatoes, sauce and water to a boil. Skim
off
foam.
Meanwhile,
cut
lean meat from bone, leaving bone
and
fat
intact.
Cube
lean
meat
into
small pieces. Add meat, bone with fat, bay leaf, garlic and seasonings to the pot.
Return to a boil; cover and simmer 2 hours. Remove bone with
fat
and
bay
leaf.
Discard.
Add celery, onions and carrots;
cook
for 15 minutes, then add potatoes, corn, beans and
macaroni.
Cook
to 20 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together.
Pour in sprayed casserole dish.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend dry ingredients in bowl until well mixed.
Combine oil, eggs, water and pumpkin and beat until well blended.
Add dry ingredients slowly and beat well.
Stir in nuts that have been dusted with reserved flour, and pour batter into greased loaf pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes (large loaves) or 60 to 65 minutes (small loaves).
Cool 10 minutes before removing.
Continue cooling.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except coconut, and microwave until good and thick.
Pour into baked pie crust.

title: christmas punch
directions: Heat cranberry juice, red hots and 1 c. water until candy is dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve hot or cold.
Yield 8 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip together cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla. Whip in peanut butter and Cool Whip.
Whip at least 5 minutes. Pour into graham cracker pie shell.

title: julie's swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together and make into meatballs. Brown in skillet.
Place	in
a large baking dish.
Cover with sauce. Bake at
for approximately 45 minutes.
Makes 35 to 40 meatballs.

title: brunch pie
directions: Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Cook	and
drain
broccoli or spinach and spread in pie plate.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
While noodles are cooking, heat margarine or butter over water bath in chafing dish until melted.
Stir in whipping cream, 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese and the salt.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until smooth.
Drain noodles; toss with cream mixture until evenly coated.
Serve with Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Makes 4 servings; 560 calories per serving.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all these fruits together and pour a large box of Jell-O instant pudding and pie filling over.
Mix well.
Let set in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: pig eaten cake
directions: Combine cake mix, mandarin oranges, eggs and oil. Beat on medium speed for 4 minutes. Pour into three greased layer cake pans or 1 oblong cake pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter, cocoa, margarine and vanilla.
Slowly bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute; remove from heat.
Add oats; beat well.
Add coconut and nuts; mix well and beat until creamy like fudge.
Drop onto heavy waxed paper with a teaspoon.
When cool, lift up with spatula.
Makes about 72 cookies.

title: barbecued beef and beans
directions: In a 6-quart electric
crockery-cooker, combine kidney beans, pinto beans, Great Northern beans, green peppers and onions. Top with beef cubes. Pour 1 cup barbecue sauce over all.
Do not mix. Cover and cook on high heat setting 1 hour.
Reduce heat setting to low and cook, covered, 5 hours.
Remove cover and stir in remaining 1/2 cup barbecue sauce. Cook, uncovered, 1/2 to 1 hour longer. Serve over split French rolls.
Preparation:
15 minutes. Cook: 6 1/2 to 7 hours. Serves 5 to 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with cornbread dressing mix. Put 1/2 of mixture in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour some broth over top. Put chicken next, then soup. Pour more broth over, then finish with rest of cornbread mixture.
Top with remaining broth.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well. Stir in milk and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Put in refrigerator.
Chill.
Roll and cut.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Decorate.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Put in baking dish; sprinkle with cheese and cover with crushed chips.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: salmon ball
directions: Combine salmon, cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish, salt and liquid smoke; make into ball.
Roll in pecans and parsley.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cut cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices. Cover bottom of 14-inch round pizza pan or 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan with slices overlapping slightly.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until crust is lightly browned.
Cool completely.

title: blondies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Stir.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: gorgonzola pizza bread
directions: On a greased baking sheet, place Boboli.
Brush oil and garlic over Boboli.
Sprinkle with tomato, Gorgonzola cheese, rosemary and oregano.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Use a large, deep dish or bowl.
Saute carrot and onion in margarine (Corning Ware is best).
Leave skin on zucchini.
Remove seeds and cut in cubes.
Add to carrot mixture and cook until tender.
Add croutons, soup and sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fat-free easy fruit cobbler
directions: Mix together until smooth and pour into 9-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Pour sweetened fruit in middle of batter. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
May use any kind of fruit.

title: easy tuna noodle casserole
directions: In large saucepan, put butter and sauteed onion.
Drain tuna in can, then add to onion.
Add mushroom soup and 3 soup cans of water.
Bring to rolling boil.
Add noodles and peas.
Turn to medium heat.
Cook until noodles are done.
Pour into serving dish and top with Mozzarella cheese and parsley.

title: no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: Cook 5 minutes after mixture boils; remove from heat.
Add oats and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix butter, egg, lemon cake mix and 1 cup of chopped pecans. Mix well, then pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, beat together until creamy cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs. Pour over crust and bake at 350° until brown.
Cool, then cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: rose petal tea
directions: Use 2 tablespoons mixture per cup.
Drink with a little sugar or honey to bring out the flavor.
Store away from light in an airtight container.
May package in cheesecloth for gift giving. Use 2 tablespoons, tie with kitchen wire and give in a large teacup.
Wrap with a linen napkin.

title: welsh rabbit
directions: Place tomato on toast slices and cover with melted cheese.

title: mother-in-law's fruit cobbler
directions: Take pan out of oven and pour batter over butter.
Pour fruit over batter; do not disturb layers.
Place in oven and bake until golden brown.
Crust will come to top.

title: pookies cookies
directions: First you take your butter, brown sugar, white sugar, eggs and vanilla and you beat it together.
Then when it is well mixed add your flour, salt and baking soda.
After that is well mixed add the chocolate chips.
Turn oven to 350°.
If cookies come out flat, add more flour.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add 2 to 3 eggs; beat.
Add 1 cup flour; beat.
Add 2 to 3 eggs; beat.
Add 1 cup flour; beat.
Add 2 eggs; beat.
Add 1 cup flour.
Add extract and sour cream.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours or until done.
Start in cold oven.

title: spiced honey
directions: Place cinnamon sticks and cloves in jar of honey.
Cap tightly.
Put honey jar in a pot and cover with hot water.
Leave in water 1 hour changing it a couple of times.
Let cool with cover still on.
Leave cloves and cinnamon sticks in honey.
Use as needed.
It makes great gifts.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Make Kool-Aid according to directions.
Make orange juice according to directions.
(Leave out some water if to be served with ice.)
Chill.
Pour in ginger ale just before serving.

title: cheesy tuna noodles
directions: Cook noodles. Saute onions in a little butter. In a bowl, combine soup and milk. Stir in tuna and cheeses. Pour over onion; drain noodles. Add to tuna mixture and mix well. Put in baking dish in oven until heated through, about 1/2 hour.

title: icebox cheese cake
directions: Crush graham crackers adding 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Mix with melted butter.
Line bottom of pan with 1/2 of the mixture (don't worry about the sides).
Save other 1/2 for the top.
Chill the milk.
Make Jell-O but only use 1 cup boiling water.
Let stand until consistency is egg white.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in a bowl by hand.
Beat chilled milk until stiff.
Drop in cheese mixture slowly and add Jell-O mixture; blend.
Pour into pan.
Put other 1/2 of graham cracker mixture on top.
Put in the refrigerator.

title: sourdough starter and bread
directions: Mix together and let stand for 8 to 12 hours.

title: beef and pepper salad
directions: Slice red and yellow peppers into 1-inch thick slices.
Slice onion paper thin.
Trim any fat from steak.
In nonstick 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in 1 tablespoon olive oil, cook red and yellow peppers until tender-crisp.
Stir in onion and cook until onion is golden brown and peppers are tender.
Remove pepper mixture to bowl.
Sprinkle steak with salt.
In same skillet in 1 tablespoon additional oil, cook steak 8 to 12 minutes until done. Remove to cutting board and slice thinly.
In drippings in skillet, cook frozen lima beans and black pepper until lima beans are lightly browned, stirring often.
Remove to bowl.
In same skillet (not over heat), mix balsamic vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, sugar and 2 tablespoons olive oil until blended.
Place lettuce in large serving bowl; top with steak, pepper mixture and lima beans.
Drizzle warm dressing over salad; toss to serve. Makes 4 servings.

title: crab cakes
directions: Heat butter or margarine in a skillet and partially cook the onion.
Remove from heat and stir in bread crumbs; combine with the crab meat.
Add a mixture of the beaten eggs and the next 5 ingredients; blend thoroughly.
Add enough cream to hold the crab meat mixture together.
Shape into 12 (2 1/2-inch) cakes.
Coat cakes with flour.
Fry in butter or oil (about 1/4 inch deep in skillet) until cakes are golden brown and cooked through, about 3 minutes per side.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: hot cider
directions: Heat cider with spices and sugar until heated through.
Add orange slices for flavor and decoration.
Ladle into cups to serve.

title: pumpkin-gingerbread trifle
directions: Bake gingerbread according to directions in 2 separate pans. Cool completely. Prepare pudding and cool completely. Stir pumpkin, brown sugar and cinnamon into pudding. Crumble one batch of gingerbread in large pretty bowl. Pour half of pudding mixture over gingerbread. Add half carton Cool Whip. Repeat with remaining gingerbread, pudding, then Cool Whip.

title: grilled or fried hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients well and cook on grill or fry.
Makes about 15 hamburgers

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix coconut and pecans together; sprinkle in bottom of pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour this over coconut and pecans.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and butter.
Spoon over cake mixture.
Cook in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Let cool. Delicious.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Mix thawed potatoes with rest of ingredients.
Put into buttered square pan 1/2 of recipe or 9 x 13-inch oblong pan for all of recipe.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine eggs, shortening and corn; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to egg mixture; mix well.
Spoon drop in hot oil.
Fry in deep fat (375°) until done.

title: roberta potatoes
directions: "Christmas at Pa and Mema's was always very special as all the cousins, aunts, uncles and friends gathered there for the festivities.
The smells when you opened the front door were intoxicating.
The huge cedar tree in the corner of the parlor room loaded with gifts was awesome.
The Christmas Jam Cake tucked away in the cupboard was another family tradition and I couldn't wait to see it, to smell it.
And most of all, to sink my teeth into that wonderful Christmas experience.
My mother has carried on the tradition and I have made the cake many times myself.
My recipe is a little different from Mothers.
Mine is a darker color because I use cocoa.
I think it's wonderful.
Here it is.
Hope it turns out as well for you."

title: best sugar cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco, brown sugar and white sugar.
Put 2 eggs, sour cream and vanilla in a cup to equal 1 cup; add to creamed mixture.
Mix.
Add rest of ingredients.
Roll 1/2-inch thick cut into your favorite shapes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add sour cream.
Stir in sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine butter, brown sugar and remaining flour.
Sprinkle over top of pie. Return to oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until filling is set.
Cool completely on a wire rack.
Serves 10.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix the first ten ingredients in large pan in order given. Drop by large tablespoonfuls.
Flatten and decorate with M&M's. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes many cookies.

title: glorified rice salad
directions: Combine cooled rice, pineapple, pecans and cherries.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.

title: old fashioned lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in double boiler.
Add egg yolks and lemon juice.
Keep mixing and gradually add water and then the butter.
Cook until filling thickens, stirring often. Cool; pour into baked pie shell.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sauce mix with 1/4 cup cold water to form a paste.
Add 3/4 cup cold water; stir until thickened.
Combine ground beef with egg, contents of bread crumb mix and 1/2 cup sauce.
Shape meat mixture into a loaf.
Place into a 9 x 5-inch or 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan or shallow baking dish.
Bake.
Drain excess fat.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Drain artichokes and chop; mix all ingredients.
Place in 1/2-quart oven-to-table baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve with crackers.
Can be prepared and refrigerated until ready to heat.

title: oven spaghetti
directions: Saute green pepper and onion until tender in butter.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, olives and oregano.
Add ground meat. Simmer, uncovered, for about 10 minutes.
Place half of spaghetti in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with half the vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle 1 cup Cheddar cheese on top.
Repeat layers.
Mix soup and water and pour over top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Cut sugar cookie roll into 32 slices and place on a pizza (round) pan. Cook according to directions on package. Cool.

title: hawaiian pineapple pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cornmeal.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in an unbaked pie crust for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and egg.
Add cinnamon, soda, flour and salt.
This mixture will be thick for there is no liquid.
Add apples and nuts.
Spread out in a flat pan and bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplins
directions: Place cleaned chicken in a deep pan.
Cover with water and season as desired.	Cover and simmer until tender.	Allow about 1 hour for a broiler-fryer and about 2 to 3 hours for a stewing hen. Sift 3 or 4 cups flour in a bowl.
Make a well in it.
Add salt, egg and water.
Make a stiff dough and let stand in refrigerator a few hours.	Roll out thin and put into boiling chicken broth and cook.

title: flat bread
directions: Roll thin.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350°.

title: chili sauce
directions: Chop all vegetables fine.
Do not put through food grinder. Mix with dry ingredients and vinegar.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours. This makes about 6 pints.
Do not double recipe or texture will not be satisfactory.

title: tossed salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shake well and let stand overnight.

title: gazpacho
directions: *Instead of olive oil, you can use 1/2 cup Kraft free Italian dressing (salad).

title: cherry crunch
directions: Put pineapple on bottom of pan; spread pie filling over it. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Cut butter into slices and add on top.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.
May top with vanilla ice cream if desired.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together the sugar and melted butter.
Add egg and beat well. Add bananas. Stir in flour and mix well. Stir in nuts.
Pour in greased loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: eggplant or squash casserole
directions: Cook squash or eggplant and salt until tender.
Mix all ingredients except 1/4 cup of cheese; mix well.
Pour into greased 1-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle rest of cheese on top and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.

title: chili sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes, peppers and onions and combine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Adjust jar rings on clean, hot jars and fill with hot sauce.
Wipe off jar rings; seal.

title: special orange salad
directions: Add jello to boiling water.
Mix on low speed the cream cheese.
Add marshmallows, carrots and pineapple.
Let set until it starts to get firm, then whip in Cool Whip.

title: guacamole salad
directions: Cover plates with greens and then alfalfa sprouts.
Process avocado, onion, lemon juice, salt and pepper in food processor or blender until smooth.
Spread on top of alfalfa sprouts.
Slice pepper into rings.
Place on avocado.
Add shrimp to center of pepper ring.
Garnish with crushed corn chips.
Serves 4 or more.

title: peachy orange froth(serves 4)
directions: Puree peaches in blender.
When smooth, add 2 juice cans of water and the remaining ingredients.
Process until frothy.
Serve immediately.
Garnish with an orange slice and mint sprig, if desired.

title: spanish tomato rice
directions: Cook onion and pepper until tender in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Crumble bacon on top and serve.

title: 60 minute batter rolls
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar.
Add shortening and cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add to milk mixture. Add flour.
Cover and set for 30 minutes in a warm place free from draft.
The batter should be double in bulk.
Knead on floured board.
Roll out to desired thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush with margarine and let rise for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° to 400° until done.

title: quick cake and fruit
directions: Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan and spread with can of fruit pie
filling.
Sprinkle box of mix over fruit.
Drizzle butter over
mix.	Bake
at
350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream (or sour cream).

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spaghetti and drain; set aside. Melt butter.
Stir in flour; add chicken broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Remove from heat.
Stir in half and half, parsley, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Toss chicken, mushrooms and spaghetti with sauce.
Turn mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes until thoroughly heated.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple betty
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup syrup.
Mix pineapple with sugar, coconut and spices.
Mix pineapple syrup and next 2 ingredients.
Spoon half the crouton mixture into shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover with half the pineapple mixture, remaining crouton mixture and the pineapple.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Line two 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans with foil.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in an egg mixer bowl.
Beat eggs on high speed of electric mixer for 4 minutes or until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually add the 1 1/2 cups of sugar and beat 4 minutes.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture, beating on low speed just until combined.
Heat the buttermilk and butter just until butter melts.
Add milk mixture, beating on low speed until combined.
Pour into pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Remove from pans.
Cut layers in half horizontally for a total of 4 layers.

title: chocolate chip cookie dessert
directions: Dip cookies in milk for a few seconds, enough to do one layer at a time.
Layer cookies in a dish.
Cover with a layer of Cool Whip.
Put another layer of dipped cookies with Cool Whip on top. Continue, ending with cookies on top.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all above ingredients, cover and chill. Serve with fresh vegetables, chips or crackers.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Cut up veggies; sprinkle with Accent and set aside.
Mix all other ingredients well.
Pour over veggies; cover.
Stir occasionally.
Put in fridge; best to let stand overnight.

title: easy dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly and place them in very hot water. In a large pot boil vinegar, water and salt for 2 minutes.
Drain hot water from cucumbers and put them in sterile jars with dill and garlic.
Pour boiling vinegar solution over cucumbers and seal jars immediately.
Store in a cool dark place, and open in 3 to 4 weeks.

title: lemon fluff
directions: In large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add ice cubes and stir until ice cubes melt. Blend in chilled whipped evaporated milk. Add chilled pineapple, grated cheese and pecans. Chill in the refrigerator until set. May be served as a salad or as a dessert. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: nutritious fruit punch
directions: Mix peaches and banana in blender.
Finely grate skin of one lemon, then juice 3 lemons.
Mix peaches, banana, lemon rind, lemon juice, pineapple juice and orange juice in a large container.
Add enough water to make 2 gallons.
Sweeten to taste.
Serve chilled.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Wash unpeeled squash; slice in 1/4-inch slices.
Cook in salted water until barely tender.
Drain well.
Put squash in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add butter, salt, pepper and onion.
Combine milk, eggs and cheese.
Mix well.
Pour over squash mixture and stir until blended.
Top with crumbs and drizzle with melted butter. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well; stir in frozen (broken up) broccoli.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
The last 15 minutes, sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top to brown.

title: beef brisket
directions: Line a large pan with heavy-duty foil about 2 1/2 times longer than the brisket.
(I use a lasagna or jelly roll pan.)
Place brisket (trim fat if necessary) in foil.
Place onion on top of meat.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat. Wrap meat loosely, but seal firmly.
Bake at 275° for 8 to 10 hours.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Mix as listed and chill overnight.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients.
In baking dish, add layer of blackberry mixture and one layer of dough.
Top with dough.
Bake 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cook whole squash in boiling water to cover, 10 minutes. Drain.
Cool to touch.
Cut squash in half lengthwise; scoop out pulp, leaving 1/4-inch shells.
Place shells into a lightly greased baking dish in a single layer.

title: pecan crunch pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Combine sugar and baking powder; beat into egg whites.
Add vanilla.
Fold in graham cracker crumbs, then pecans.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pie plate and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool.

title: chocolate turtle cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and butter.
Press onto bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels in milk in heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently until smooth (or melt in microwave; stir to smooth). Pour over crust.
Top with pecans.

title: unbelievable salad
directions: Pour the pineapple with its juice into a small saucepan; heat until juice comes to a boil. Remove from heat. Pour gelatin mix into large glass mixing bowl. Pour pineapple and juice into gelatin. Stir until gelatin is dissolved. Chill until cool and begins to thicken, about 2 hours. Stir in oranges, cottage cheese and whipped topping. Pour into an 8-inch square dish. Refrigerate until firm. Cut into squares and serve. Serves 6.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Place all spices into a cheesecloth or a tea ball.
Put spice ball into crock-pot with cider and brown sugar.
Keep spices in for 2 hours.
Or, place cider into an electric percolator and put spices and brown sugar in the basket.

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt candy in double boiler. Mix (by hand) in Cool Whip. Pour into pie shells and cool. Refrigerate. Makes 2 pies.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown together the first 4 ingredients.
Then add sugar, vinegar and catsup.
Simmer for about 1 hour.

title: chicken puffs
directions: Bring water and butter to a boil.
Add flour and salt.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth after each. Place a level tablespoon of batter on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: vegetable pasta
directions: Cook rotelle to desired doneness, adding broccoli during last 2 minutes.	Drain, rinse with cold water.
Drain well.
Combine all ingredients with cooked rotelle and broccoli; mix well. Refrigerate 2 hours to blend flavors.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream the butter, peanut butter and sugars. Add egg and vanilla.
Beat until creamy. Stir in dry ingredients until blended.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls. Press into 1 1/2-inch muffin tins. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Remove from oven and immediately press one miniature peanut butter cup candy into each hot cookie crust.
Allow to cool.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Mix with Cool Whip, cottage cheese and dry jello.
Add coconut and chopped pecans, if desired. Store in refrigerator.
Salad is ready to eat immediately, but is better after refrigeration.

title: beefy hash brown pizza
directions: In a bowl, combine the potatoes, soup, egg, salt and pepper. Spread mixture into a greased 15 x 10-inch baking pan. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chicken a la coque
directions: Brown chicken in frying pan.
Cut mushrooms in half.
Saute in butter.
In a saucepan, heat mushroom and chicken soups with milk; add sauteed mushrooms.
Place chicken in a baking dish, arranging so that the sauce covers chicken evenly.
Bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: apricot chiffon pie
directions: Mix apricots, sugar and cinnamon.
Cover with hot water and let stand until apricots soften.
Cook until tender.
Mix cornstarch	and
cold
water.
Add	to apricots and cook until thick.
Puree while hot.

title: apple goodies
directions: Mix cake mix, butter or margarine and coconut or nuts.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Add pie filling and top with sugar cinnamon mixture.
Mix sour cream and egg.
Pour over pie filling.
Bake 30 minutes more at 350°. Cool, cut and enjoy.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt the caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Combine in a bowl the cake mix, margarine, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and the pecans.
Stir with spoon until dough holds together.

title: sweet potatoes with cranberries
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, oats and cinnamon.
Cut in butter with mixture until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Toss 1 cup of crumb mixture with sweet potatoes and cranberries.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
After baking, add 1 1/2 c. marshmallows; broil until brown.

title: salmon dill mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and lemon juice.
Chill until thickened.
Mix salmon with remaining ingredients.
Blend into thickened gelatin.
Pour into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Unmold. Garnish with dill and thinly sliced cucumber, if desired.
Makes 5 1/3 cups of 6 to 8 servings.

title: milky way cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Melt candy bars and butter, stirring frequently, in double boiler. Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar.
Combine egg yolks, buttermilk and baking soda in a small bowl until blended. Combine flour and salt in another bowl.
Add to candy mixture alternately. Stir in pecans.
In a clean mixer bowl, beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Fold into batter.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake 1 1/4 hours. Cool for 15 minutes.
Unmold and cool completely.
Melt chocolate in double boiler. Drizzle over cooled cake.

title: caramel corn
directions: Blend butter and syrup bring to a boil in a double boiler. Add vanilla.
Add soda; pour over popcorn.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Set aside. In 12-inch skillet, cook ground beef and onion over medium heat until meat is brown, stirring occasionally. Discard drippings. Add next 6 ingredients. Simmer 20 minutes, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until most of liquid is evaporated. Pour 1/2 cup taco sauce into casserole. Arrange half tortillas (thawed) to cover, overlapping if necessary. Pour 1/2 cup taco sauce evenly over tortillas. Spoon in beef mixture. Top with sour cream and sprinkle on half of the cheese. Arrange remaining tortillas, overlapping slightly on cheese. Spread remaining taco sauce over tortillas and sprinkle on rest of cheese. Cover with foil and bake 40 minutes. Remove foil and bake 5 more minutes. Serves 8 (about 515 calories per serving).

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and melt margarine.
Mix dry ingredients. Add all together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 350° until filling is firm.

title: festive egg squares
directions: Layer sausage, mushrooms, green onions, tomatoes and cheese in greased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Beat remaining ingredients and pour over sausage mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven about 30 minutes until golden brown and set.
Cut into 12 (3-inch) squares.
Serves 12.
Good for brunch.

title: scrumptious salad
directions: In a small saucepan over medium heat, cook and stir almonds with sugar; cook until almonds are coated and slightly brown. Spread the coated almonds on foil and cool completely, then break apart gently.
In large bowl, combine lettuce, oranges, celery and onions.
Top with the almonds.
Pour dressing over salad and gently toss. Serves 8.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute
onions
in
oleo until golden; add hominy, Cheez Whiz and
soup.	Mix
well.
Pour
into	1 1/2 quart casserole dish; sprinkle
with
Fritos.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Spray casserole dish with Pam before pouring the hominy into it.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Heat milk in saucepan over medium heat.
Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add sugar mixture to hot milk, stirring constantly. Cook until thick.
Lower heat. Add egg yolks and cook 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add butter. Cool slightly while making the meringue. Add vanilla to cream mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell.
Cover with the meringue and sprinkle with coconut. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix
all ingredients and then add 4 eggs, one at a time. Pour into
a
greased and floured Bundt mold in which you have sprinkled chopped pecans.

title: oven barbecued ribs
directions: Place ribs in shallow roasting pan, meaty side up.
(Trim as much fat off as possible).
Place a slice of unpeeled lemon and thin slice of onion on each serving piece.
Roast in oven at 400° for 30 minutes (longer if using country-style ribs).
Pour off any fat.

title: caraway's vegetable soup(makes 12 quarts)
directions: Place stew beef in large pot. Cover with water. Salt to taste. Boil for 30 minutes. Add peas, butter beans and carrots. Let boil until almost tender and then add okra, cabbage and hamburger (leave some in small balls of meat). Let come to a boil and add tomatoes and corn. Simmer on low heat, adding water as needed. Season to taste with salt, pepper and sugar. When done, add tomato soup for more color and flavor. When cool, place in containers for freezing.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Cook about 1 hour on low until soft ball forms in cool water. Let set; do not stir until cool, 20 to 25 minutes.
Beat until thick, about 10 minutes.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: southwest chicken soup
directions: Saute' in oil the onions and celery until soft.
Add stock, chicken and brown rice.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and cook until chicken is tender (20-30 minutes).
Remove chicken and set aside until cool; remove bones and shred.
Add to stock along with remaining ingredients.
Serves 6-8.

title: candy oatmeal drops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat the shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla together until creamy.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with milk.
Stir in oats and candy.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: squash and corn casserole
directions: Slice squash about 1/2-inch thick.
Cook until done.
Drain well.
Mash with butter, salt, pepper and onion.
Add dressing, eggs and corn.
Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with dressing and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Soften yeast in warm water and set aside.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut shortening into flour mixture.
Add milk and softened yeast.
Stir until well blended.
Store in refrigerator about 1 hour before baking.
Roll dough 1/2 inch thick and cut using a 2 inch cutter.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces into melted margarine, then into mixture of dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not turn chicken.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Lightly toss cucumbers with 1 tsp. salt. Chill well.
Meanwhile combine sour cream, lemon juice, remaining salt, sugar and pepper.
Drain cucumbers.
Toss with sour cream mixture.
Refrigerate about 2 hours.
Turn cucumbers into shallow serving bowl.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serve.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Heat on low flame and stir until nuts are coated good.
Pour onto paper towels and separate to cool.
Can be stored in can or jar for later.

title: peanut butter rice krispies
directions: Mix sugar and syrup (heat together). Add peanut butter. Pour over Rice Krispies.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine oil, eggs and sugar in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer 2 minutes.

title: fudge nut pie
directions: Cream butter, gradually beat in sugar and beat until fluffy. Add egg yolks and vanilla; blend well.
Add melted chocolate mixture.
Add walnuts.
Turn into pie shell.
Bake in hot, 375°, oven for 30 to 35 minutes, or until puffed across top.
Cool. Serve with vanilla ice cream, or with whipped cream or topping.

title: banana split cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in a 14 x 18-inch greased pan at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: baked spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach following directions; drain well.
Set aside. Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine eggs, cheese, butter, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in spinach and stuffing mix.
Shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake about 10 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In a 2 quart casserole dish, mix the macaroni with the mayonnaise, soup and Cheddar cheese.
In a mixing bowl, combine butter and crackers; spread over the macaroni mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: green pea salad
directions: Drain peas. Add all ingredients together. Mix lightly but well so you don't mash the peas. Serve cold. Store leftovers in covered container in refrigerator. Add mayonnaise (more or less) according to desired taste. Makes 8 servings. Preparation time: 0:30.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies (or blend on high, about 5 at a time).
The crushed Oreos are your dirt.
Combine softened cream cheese and softened butter with powdered sugar.
Set aside.
Mix pudding with milk until it thickens.
Fold in the cream cheese mixture with the pudding and whipped topping.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cut-up cabbage in boiling water until almost tender. Drain.
Put half of the cabbage in bottom of a greased 2-quart casserole reserving the rest for the top.
Mix all the rest of the ingredients together, except the milk and remaining cabbage.
Put into casserole.
Pour milk over it.
Put cabbage on top.
Dot with butter.
Do not cover.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours. Watch so the cabbage doesn't get too burned on top.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, oil, egg, salt and flour; mix until well blended.
Put in refrigerator.
When ready to use, place by spoonfuls into well-greased muffin pans.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
These will keep in refrigerator for one week.

title: kielbasa and rice
directions: In skillet, saute onions and peppers.
Add tomatoes, water and sugar.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Prepare rice while this is cooking. Cut sausage into rounds and add along with rice to skillet. Simmer, covered, 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: pizza pies
directions: Turn oven to 450°.
With scissors, cut circles out of pita bread.
Only cut the top portion out, don't go all the way through. Spread tomato sauce on bread with spoon.
Grate cheese and pour over top the sauce.
Sprinkle pies evenly with basil and oregano. Then add any extra toppings.
Place pies on a cookie sheet or baking pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until cheese melts, then toast the pita bread circle in microwave or toaster and place on top of the pizza.

title: oriental rice
directions: Slice bell pepper, carrots and onion into thin strips.
Chop green onion.
Lightly brown ground beef.
Heat wok on low heat, add 2 tablespoons oil.
Mix ground beef, shrimp and chicken in oil and heat for approximately 2 minutes.
Add vegetables and cook until tender, stirring constantly.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: toscana soup
directions: Combine stock and cream in a saucepan over medium heat. Slice unpeeled potato into 1/4 inch slices and add to soup.
Add kale.
Saute sausage.
When sausage is done, cool and cut at angle into slices about 1/4 inch thick.
Add sausage to soup.
Add salt and pepper flakes; let soup simmer for about 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: pop-up surprise
directions: Mix together cream cheese, mayo and dressing.
Roll out crescent rolls on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 400° for approximately 10 minutes.
Cool and spread cream cheese, mayo and dressing over crust, then sprinkle on chopped vegetables and cut into squares.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first six ingredients in order listed into a 9X13 dish. Mix Miracle Whip and sour cream together and spread on top of salad. Top off with cheese and bacon.

title: donald's chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onion, celery and carrots in butter for 10 minutes.
Add flour to sauteed mixture, stirring well.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Combine broth and milk; gradually stir into vegetable mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Add chopped chicken, stirring well.
Pour chicken mixture into a shallow 2-quart casserole.
Top with pastry and cut slits for steam.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: diann's salsa
directions: Chop chilies, Ro-Tel tomatoes, onion, cilantro, avocado and jalapeno peppers.
Mix with crushed tomatoes.
Refrigerate for several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with tortilla chips or fresh vegetables as a dip.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients except the pie shell in a blender.
Pour mixture into pie shell and bake in a 350° oven until custard thickens (approximately 30 minutes).
You may use egg substitute if you are watching your cholesterol.
If you do not have a pie shell, this recipe is good baked in a pie plate.
This recipe is from Billy's mother, Margaret Majors.

title: beer bread
directions: You will also need vegetable cooking spray.

title: diet cole slaw
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour over shredded cabbage.

title: party time cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, Accent, Worcestershire sauce, onions, and 3 jars of dried beef.
Use last jar of dried beef to roll cheese ball in.
(This is better if made several days in advance.)

title: coconut orange jumbles
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Add egg yolk and coconut; beat well.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to the creamed mixture alternately with orange juice.
After each addition, beat until smooth.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with additional coconut and grated orange peel.
Bake in a moderate 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 50.

title: broccoli cheese bake
directions: Cook broccoli cuts until crisp.
Mix mayonnaise, mushroom soup, eggs and cheese with electric mixer until blended.
Add drained broccoli and mushrooms to mayonnaise/egg mixture.
Place in 8-inch square or 2-quart baking dish.
Top with crushed crackers mixed with melted margarine.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: aunt peg and aunt verlee's peach cobbler
directions: This is one of my favorites.
It's simple and very good. Summer visits to Winston Salem always held the smell of boxwoods and warm peach cobbler.

title: window cleaner
directions: Mix and put in spray bottle.

title: oven-fried potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and cut each into 1/8-inch wedges.
Place wedges slightly overlapping in a single layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well. Brush potatoes with half of the oil mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes, basting occasionally with remaining seasoned oil mixture. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: confectioners sugar frosting
directions: In small bowl, mix well confectioners sugar, water and vanilla until smooth and of desired consistency.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly; place in a loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Drain grease; top with ketchup. Makes 4 servings.

title: banana split pie
directions: Melt margarine in 9-inch pie plate and mix crumbs to form crust.
Bake at 350 for 12 - 15 minutes and let cool.
Meanwhile mix pudding and milk and let chill.
Also drain pineapple and chill.
When ready to assembly pie, slice banana over bottom of crust.
Next spread pineapple over banana and chilled pudding over pineapple.
Spread whipped topping over all and garnish.
Makes 8 servings.
Each serving is 1 bread, 1/4 milk, 1/2 fruit, 2 fat.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Pour 1/3 of sauce into a 7 x 11-inch baking dish; stir 1/4 cup water into remaining sauce, add seasonings and set aside.
Layer noodles and cover with sauce.
Crumble uncooked beef, 1/2 of shredded Co-Jack and 1/3 of sauce.
Arrange noodles with rest of Co-Jack cheese and cottage cheese and pour rest of sauce over top. Cover with double layer of Saran Wrap.
Cook in microwave at 1/2 power for 10 minutes. Turn. Cook at 1/2 power for 10 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Turn.
Cook at Full Power 7 minutes, turn and cook at Full Power for 7 minutes.
Uncover.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Cook at Full Power for 2 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes before cutting.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Peel cool eggs. Wrap each egg with sufficient sausage to make a ball around the egg. Brush with egg and roll in bread crumbs. Place in refrigerator to chill. (Will keep overnight.) Place eggs in a heavy skillet with 1-inch of hot grease. Fry until sausage is done. Drain and cut eggs in half lengthwise. Serve immediately.

title: skillet beef pilaf
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oil.
Add meat, crumbled, and let brown.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add rice and stir over low heat until rice looks translucent (approximately 3 minutes). Add broth slowly; cover and simmer until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed (approximately 20 minutes).
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese if desired.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix together and top off with pecan pieces and maraschino cherries.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix
soup,
cheese
and tomatoes together and pour over hominy.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Crumble chips on top.

title: applesauce banana bread
directions: Mix bananas and sugar together and let set for 15 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and beat all together, mixing well. Pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until center is set.
Cool.
This recipe is fat-free.

title: bible cake
directions: Leaven means baking powder.

title: cheese rounds
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on bread.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until bubbly.

title: frozen cranberry ring
directions: Combine gelatin and water; chill until beginning to set.
Whip the cranberry juice; fold sauce and lemon juice into thickened gelatin.
Set aside.

title: chicken divan(great for lots of people)
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour, stirring, until bubbly. Add chicken broth, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add sherry, nutmeg and some pepper.
Fold in whipped cream.
Add cheese and stir for 2 minutes, until melted.

title: spinach-chicken pasta casserole(heart healthy)
directions: Thaw spinach; drain.
Prepare mostaccioli.
Spray nonstick skillet with Pam spray.
Saute onions and garlic; add chicken cubes for 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer (no cover) 5 minutes.

title: oreo pie
